{"type":"assistant","uuid":"2026031304293768c2f8d899a84264","session_id":"301af3e8-7399-4356-b525-ec1e2117384a","message":{"id":"2026031304293768c2f8d899a84264","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019ce3bd9e3402ee324eea8410b88a41","name":"Glob","input":{"path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/tests","pattern":"**/*.test.js"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":35488,"output_tokens":157,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"__timestamp":"2026-03-12T20:29:41.305Z","_requestId":"0c0e04bf5f3f4ac585730d0e5b893431"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"4060587a-1b78-4b0a-9e9d-1436bf557340","session_id":"301af3e8-7399-4356-b525-ec1e2117384a","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019ce3bd9877070f1da4ef12d9f7b155","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L2\n   2→MODULE: security\n   3→PATH: src/security/**\n   4→DESCRIPTION: Security guard layer for permission tiers, param sanitization, and confirmation flow\n   5→\n   6→KEY_FILES:\n   7→- src/security/index.js -> module exports\n   8→- src/security/permission-guard.js -> role hierarchy and command authorization\n   9→- src/security/param-sanitizer.js -> parameter sanitization and dangerous pattern detection\n  10→- src/security/confirmation-manager.js -> confirmation flow for high-risk actions\n  11→- src/security/guard.js -> existing user authorization\n  12→- src/security/system-guard.js -> system exec authorization\n  13→\n  14→INTERFACES:\n  15→- getUserRole(userId) -> 'admin' | 'operator' | 'viewer'\n  16→- checkCommandPermission(userId, command) -> { allowed, requiresConfirmation, reason }\n  17→- isAdmin(userId) -> boolean\n  18→- sanitizeParam(input, options) -> { ok, value?, error? }\n  19→- validatePath(path, allowedRoots) -> { ok, resolved?, error? }\n  20→- detectDangerousPatterns(input) -> { safe, patterns }\n  21→- createConfirmation(userId, action, params, timeoutMs) -> { confirmId, message }\n  22→- checkConfirmation(confirmId, userId) -> { status, action?, params? }\n  23→- confirmAction(confirmId, userId) -> { ok, action?, params?, error? }\n  24→- cancelConfirmation(confirmId, userId) -> void\n  25→- logAuditEntry(entry) -> Promise<void>\n  26→- queryAuditLogs(filters) -> Promise<Object[]>\n  27→- checkCommandBlacklist(command, blacklist) -> { blocked, reason?, matchedCommand? }\n  28→- detectHighRiskKeywords(command, keywords) -> { isHighRisk, detectedKeywords }\n  29→\n  30→ROLE_HIERARCHY:\n  31→- viewer: 0 -> can view status and logs\n  32→- operator: 1 -> can run pipelines and retry\n  33→- admin: 2 -> can stop, reset, force-unlock, exec\n  34→\n  35→COMMAND_PERMISSIONS:\n  36→- status, logs, more, ls, tree, cat, head, tail, find: viewer\n  37→- pipeline, bugfix, planner, retry, cd, upload, download: operator\n  38→- stop, reset, force-unlock, exec: admin\n  39→\n  40→HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS:\n  41→- stop, reset, force-unlock -> require confirmation (CONFIRM text)\n  42→- admin can skip confirmation with --force flag\n  43→\n  44→DANGEROUS_PATTERNS:\n  45→- path traversal (..)\n  46→- shell injection (backticks, $(), ${})\n  47→- command chains (||, &&, ;)\n  48→- home directory expansion (~)\n  49→- exec/eval flags\n  50→\n  51→AUDIT_LOG:\n  52→- format: JSON Lines (.jsonl)\n  53→- fields: timestamp, userId, role, action, params, result, reason, sessionId\n  54→- rotation: max 10MB per file, max 5 files\n  55→\n  56→TRAPS:\n  57→- unknown users default to 'operator' role\n  58→- permission denied is logged before returning error\n  59→- confirmation expires after 60 seconds\n  60→- audit log write failures are silent (non-blocking)\n  61→- param sanitizer rejects all dangerous patterns regardless of context\n  62→\n  63→DEPENDS_ON:\n  64→- src/config.js -> USER_PERMISSIONS, ALLOW_ADMIN_SKIP_CONFIRM, AUDIT_LOG_*, COMMAND_BLACKLIST, HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS, DIRECT_EXEC_MODE\n  65→\n  66→DECISIONS:\n  67→- 2026-03-16 | f009-security-extensions | add checkCommandBlacklist and detectHighRiskKeywords to system-guard.js for command blacklist and high-risk keyword detection\n  68→- 2026-03-13 | F-010-file-validation | extend validatePath to support session cwd resolution, symlink resolution, and file operation audit logging\n  69→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce3bd9877070f1da4ef12d9f7b155","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T20:29:41.306Z","_requestId":"0c0e04bf5f3f4ac585730d0e5b893431"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"e1c76f88-8e3b-4167-b334-ab68ba0f5bbd","session_id":"301af3e8-7399-4356-b525-ec1e2117384a","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019ce3bd9a4bad04057188fd25d72c3c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L2\n   2→MODULE: runtime/services\n   3→PATH: src/services/**\n   4→DESCRIPTION: runtime service layer for chat/session/system actions plus pipeline control facade\n   5→\n   6→KEY_FILES:\n   7→- src/services/chat-service.js\n   8→- src/services/chat-queue.js\n   9→- src/services/session-store.js\n  10→- src/services/realtime-hub.js\n  11→- src/services/system-exec-service.js\n  12→- src/services/pipeline-control-service.js\n  13→- src/services/pipeline-controller.js\n  14→- src/services/plan-ingestion-service.js\n  15→- src/services/status-aggregator.js\n  16→- src/services/log-pager.js\n  17→- src/services/telegram-pusher.js\n  18→- src/services/git-service.js\n  19→- src/services/commit-service.js\n  20→- src/services/command-executor-service.js\n  21→- src/services/output-pager-service.js\n  22→- src/services/file-service.js\n  23→\n  24→PUBLIC_APIS:\n  25→- chatWithSession({ channel, sessionId, message, realtimeHooks })\n  26→- resetSession({ channel, sessionId })\n  27→- pipeline control: startPipeline/getPipelineStatus/stopPipeline/retryTarget/getPipelineLogs/resetTarget\n  28→- pipeline controller (F-004): createPipelineController -> startPipeline/stopPipeline/retryTarget/runSingle/getStatus/getLogs/forceUnlock\n  29→- plan ingestion: validate/save/listVersions/getVersion/setCurrent/getCurrent/rollback/getActivePath\n  30→- status aggregator (F-005): createStatusAggregator -> aggregateStatus/formatStatusForTelegram/calculateProgress/getErrorSummary\n  31→- log pager (F-005): createLogPager -> readLogPage/extractErrorLines/shouldSendAsFile/formatLogsForTelegram\n  32→- telegram pusher (F-005): createTelegramPusher -> startHeartbeat/stopHeartbeat/pushErrorSummary/sendMessageChunked/sendFile\n  33→- git service (F-008): createGitService -> getStatus/isClean/getChangedFiles/commit/amendCommit/getLastCommit/getCommitLog/getShortHash\n  34→- commit service (F-008): createCommitService -> validatePreConditions/commit/recordCommit/getSessionCommits/checkPipelineStatus/checkTestStatus/buildCommitMessage\n  35→- command executor (F-009): executeCommand/confirmHighRiskCommand -> blacklist check, high-risk detection, confirmation flow, cwd support, output pagination\n  36→- output pager (F-009): paginateOutput/storeOutputPages/getNextPage/clearPages/hasMorePages -> Telegram 4096 char limit handling\n  37→- file service (F-010): validatePath/resolveSessionPath/listDirectory/buildTree/readFile/searchFiles/writeFile/isBinaryFile -> file operations with path validation\n  38→\n  39→TRAPS:\n  40→- chat operations are serialized by session key; keep async queue semantics unchanged\n  41→- pipeline-control-service must delegate to script-runner instead of shell string concatenation\n  42→- pipeline-controller must use lock-manager for concurrency protection (F-004)\n  43→- runSingle must NOT acquire lock (independent execution, D5)\n  44→- file-service validatePath checks against config.telegramFileAllowedRoots (frozen at startup)\n  45→- file-service resolves symlinks and re-validates against allowed roots for security\n  46→\n  47→DECISIONS:\n  48→- 2026-03-10 | f001-pipeline-service | expose logs/reset methods in pipeline-control-service to satisfy US3 reusable control surface\n  49→- 2026-03-12 | f003-plan-ingestion | add plan-ingestion-service for schema validation, version management, and plan registry\n  50→- 2026-03-12 | f004-pipeline-controller | new module for unified pipeline control with lock management (D4)\n  51→- 2026-03-13 | f005-status-logs | add status-aggregator, log-pager, telegram-pusher for pipeline status aggregation and log streaming\n  52→- 2026-03-15 | f008-commit-workflow | add git-service and commit-service for commit workflow with pre-commit validation, audit logging (AC-5.3)\n  53→- 2026-03-15 | f008-exception-handling | add try-catch blocks in commit() function around validatePreConditions, gitService.commit/amendCommit, recordCommit, logAuditEntry calls to prevent crashes and ensure errors logged to audit trail\n  54→- 2026-03-16 | f009-command-executor | add command-executor-service and output-pager-service for general shell command execution with blacklist, high-risk keywords, confirmation flow, session cwd, and pagination\n  55→- 2026-03-13 | f010-file-service | add file-service for directory listing, tree building, file reading/writing, and glob search with path validation\n  56→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce3bd9a4bad04057188fd25d72c3c","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T20:29:41.307Z","_requestId":"0c0e04bf5f3f4ac585730d0e5b893431"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"50ade2f4-d551-4e9a-a211-3b1b4d1bf426","session_id":"301af3e8-7399-4356-b525-ec1e2117384a","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019ce3bd9c520c880ac2a181e0822fd1","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L2\n   2→MODULE: bot\n   3→PATH: src/bot/**\n   4→DESCRIPTION: Telegram bot handlers and command routing layer\n   5→\n   6→ENTRYPOINT:\n   7→- src/bot/telegram.js -> createTelegramBot() registers all commands and handlers\n   8→\n   9→KEY_FILES:\n  10→- src/bot/telegram.js - Main bot factory, command registration, text handler\n  11→- src/bot/commands/index.js - Router entry point, routeCommand()\n  12→- src/bot/commands/parser.js - Command text parser, parseCommand()\n  13→- src/bot/commands/registry.js - Command registration and lookup\n  14→- src/bot/commands/validator.js - Parameter validation\n  15→- src/bot/commands/formatter.js - Error message formatting\n  16→- src/bot/commands/help.js - Help text generation\n  17→- src/bot/commands/handlers/*.js - Individual command handlers\n  18→\n  19→SUBDIRS:\n  20→- src/bot/commands -> command routing and dispatch\n  21→- src/bot/commands/handlers -> individual command implementations\n  22→\n  23→INTERFACES:\n  24→- Telegram Commands:\n  25→  - /start - Bot startup greeting\n  26→  - /help - Dynamic help text\n  27→  - /reset - Clear chat session\n  28→  - /screenshot - Capture desktop screenshot\n  29→  - /exec <cmd> - Execute system command\n  30→  - /pipeline [action] [target] [--type=] - Pipeline management (alias: /p)\n  31→  - /bugfix <target> - Start bugfix pipeline (alias: /b)\n  32→  - /planner [action] [target] - Planner pipeline management\n  33→  - /status [--type=feature|bugfix] - Show aggregated pipeline status (alias: /s)\n  34→  - /logs [--lines=N] [--offset=N] [--type=feature|bugfix] [--file] - View pipeline logs with pagination (alias: /l)\n  35→  - /stop [target] - Stop pipeline\n  36→  - /plan [action] [type] [version] - Plan file management (status/versions/use/rollback/validate)\n  37→  - /commit [--message=\"...\"] [--amend] [--force] - Commit code changes with pre-commit validation (alias: /c)\n  38→  - /commits [--count=N] - View session commit history (alias: /history)\n  39→- /cd <path> - Change session working directory (F-009)\n  40→- /more - View next page of paginated output (F-009)\n  41→- /ls [path] - List directory contents (alias: /dir) (F-010)\n  42→- /tree [path] - Display directory tree structure (F-010)\n  43→- /cat <file> - View file content (F-010)\n  44→- /head [N] <file> - View first N lines of file (F-010)\n  45→- /tail [N] <file> - View last N lines of file (F-010)\n  46→- /find <pattern> - Search files by name/glob pattern (F-010)\n  47→- /upload <path> - Upload file to specified path (F-010)\n  48→- /download <file> - Download file to Telegram (F-010)\n  49→\n  50→TRAPS:\n  51→- Commands require authorization via isAllowedUser()\n  52→- Large logs (>=4000 chars) sent as files\n  53→- Command parsing normalizes to lowercase\n  54→- Registry stores normalized command names\n  55→- F002-CRIT-001: Parser treats first non-option token as subcommand; validator must check if command has no subcommands and use parsed.subcommand as first positional param\n  56→- F-005: /status uses status-aggregator for aggregated status; /logs uses log-pager for pagination\n  57→- F-008: /commit requires pre-commit validation (pipeline status + test status); --amend/--force require admin + confirmation\n  58→\n  59→DECISIONS:\n  60→- 2026-03-12 | F-002-bot-commands | Add command routing layer with parser, registry, validator for pipeline commands\n  61→- 2026-03-12 | F-002-alias-mapping | Support command aliases /p, /b, /s, /l\n  62→- 2026-03-12 | F002-CRIT-001 | Fix positional args: validator uses parsed.subcommand as first positional when command has no subcommands\n  63→- 2026-03-12 | F-003-plan-command | Add /plan command with status/versions/use/rollback/validate subcommands for plan file management\n  64→- 2026-03-13 | F-005-status-logs | Update /status and /logs to use status-aggregator and log-pager with pagination support\n  65→- 2026-03-15 | F-008-commit-commands | Add /commit and /commits commands with pre-commit validation, session tracking, and admin confirmation for --amend/--force\n  66→- 2026-03-16 | F-009-command-executor | Add /cd and /more commands for session cwd management and paginated output viewing; add direct text mode for shell execution\n  67→- 2026-03-13 | F-010-file-manager | Add /ls, /tree, /cat, /head, /tail, /find, /upload, /download commands for file system operations with security sandbox\n  68→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce3bd9c520c880ac2a181e0822fd1","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T20:29:41.308Z","_requestId":"0c0e04bf5f3f4ac585730d0e5b893431"}
