{"type":"assistant","uuid":"202603130429539af218ab5fd1469b","session_id":"301af3e8-7399-4356-b525-ec1e2117384a","message":{"id":"202603130429539af218ab5fd1469b","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019ce3bdd70597165465c38ded9593a0","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# F-012: System Monitor - Context Snapshot\n\n## Section 1 — Feature Brief\n\n### Description\n系统信息查看与监控能力，让用户随时了解电脑的运行状态。通过 Telegram 命令获取 CPU、内存、磁盘、网络等系统指标，查看进程列表，管理进程生命周期。\n\n### Commands Design\n- `/sysinfo` - 返回系统概览（CPU 使用率、内存占用、磁盘空间、系统运行时间、网络状态）\n- `/ps` - 返回进程列表支持按 CPU/内存排序和过滤\n- `/kill <pid>` - 终止进程（需权限确认，集成 F-006）\n- `/monitor set cpu>80` - 设置阈值告警，超过阈值时自动推送通知到 Telegram\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n1. `/sysinfo` 返回 CPU、内存、磁盘、网络的当前状态摘要，格式化为可读表格\n2. `/ps` 返回进程列表，支持按 CPU/内存排序，支持过滤关键词\n3. `/kill` 可终止指定进程，执行前需权限确认（集成 F-006 权限系统）\n4. 支持设置监控阈值（如 CPU>80%），超过阈值时自动推送告警到 Telegram\n5. 告警规则持久化存储，Bot 重启后自动恢复监控\n6. 系统信息展示适配 Telegram 消息格式，信息密度高且可读性好\n\n### Dependencies\n- F-009 - General Command Executor (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Section 2 — Project Structure\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── adapters/\n├── bot/\n│   ├── commands/\n│   │   ├── handlers/      # Command handlers\n│   │   ├── parser.js\n│   │   ├── registry.js\n│   │   ├── validator.js\n│   │   └── index.js\n│   └── telegram.js\n├── config.js\n├── http/\n├── pipeline-infra/\n├── routes/\n├── security/\n│   ├── permission-guard.js\n│   ├── confirmation-manager.js\n│   └── system-guard.js\n├── services/\n│   ├── session-store.js\n│   ├── command-executor-service.js\n│   └── ...\n└── utils/\n    ├── markdown-v2-formatter.js\n    └── ...\ntests/\n├── bot/commands/handlers/\n├── services/\n├── security/\n└── ...\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 3 — Prizm Context\n\n### root.prizm (L0)\n```prizm\nDOC_LEVEL: L0\nPROJECT_NAME: PrizmClaw\nPROJECT_TYPE: telegram-bridge + web-api\nADOPTION_MODE: brownfield\nPLATFORM: codebuddy\nLANGUAGES: JavaScript(ESM), HTML, CSS, Python, Shell\nPACKAGE_MANAGER: npm\nENTRYPOINTS: src/index.js -> src/http/server.js + src/bot/telegram.js\n```\n\n### runtime.prizm (L1) - Relevant Excerpts\n```prizm\nINTERFACES:\n- Telegram: /start, /help, /reset, /screenshot, /exec, /cd, /more, /ls, /tree, /cat, /head, /tail, /find, /upload, /download, text message relay\n- Security: PermissionGuard, ParamSanitizer, ConfirmationManager, AuditLogService, SystemGuard\n\nTRAPS:\n- F-009: high-risk command keywords trigger confirmation flow (rm -rf, sudo, etc.)\n- F-009: blacklist commands are rejected before execution\n- permission check happens before command handler execution\n```\n\n### security.prizm (L2) - Key Interfaces\n```prizm\nINTERFACES:\n- getUserRole(userId) -> 'admin' | 'operator' | 'viewer'\n- checkCommandPermission(userId, command) -> { allowed, requiresConfirmation, reason }\n- isAdmin(userId) -> boolean\n- createConfirmation(userId, action, params, timeoutMs) -> { confirmId, message }\n- confirmAction(confirmId, userId) -> { ok, action?, params?, error? }\n- logAuditEntry(entry) -> Promise<void>\n\nROLE_HIERARCHY:\n- viewer: 0 -> can view status and logs\n- operator: 1 -> can run pipelines and retry\n- admin: 2 -> can stop, reset, force-unlock, exec\n\nCOMMAND_PERMISSIONS:\n- status, logs, more, ls, tree, cat, head, tail, find: viewer\n- pipeline, bugfix, planner, retry, cd, upload, download: operator\n- stop, reset, force-unlock, exec: admin\n```\n\n### services.prizm (L2) - Patterns\n```prizm\nPUBLIC_APIS:\n- command executor (F-009): executeCommand/confirmHighRiskCommand -> blacklist check, high-risk detection, confirmation flow, cwd support, output pagination\n- output pager (F-009): paginateOutput/storeOutputPages/getNextPage/clearPages/hasMorePages\n\nTRAPS:\n- file-service validatePath checks against config.telegramFileAllowedRoots (frozen at startup)\n```\n\n### bot.prizm (L2) - Command Registration Pattern\n```prizm\nINTERFACES:\n- Telegram Commands:\n  - /cd <path> - Change session working directory (F-009)\n  - /more - View next page of paginated output (F-009)\n\nTRAPS:\n- Commands require authorization via isAllowedUser()\n- Command parsing normalizes to lowercase\n- Registry stores normalized command names\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 4 — Existing Source Files\n\n### src/config.js\n```javascript\nimport 'dotenv/config';\nimport { z } from 'zod';\n\nimport { loadPipelineInfraConfig } from './pipeline-infra/config-loader.js';\nimport { resolveDaemonLogPaths } from './pipeline-infra/path-policy.js';\n\nconst schema = z.object({\n  TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  ENABLE_TELEGRAM: z.string().optional().default('true'),\n  // ... other config options\n  // F-009: General Command Executor\n  COMMAND_BLACKLIST: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS: z.string().optional().default('rm -rf,sudo,kill,chmod -R,chown,dd,mkfs,shutdown,reboot,halt'),\n  DIRECT_EXEC_MODE: z.string().optional().default('false'),\n  // F-011: AI CLI Proxy\n  AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_THRESHOLD_MS: z.coerce.number().int().nonnegative().default(10000),\n  AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_MS: z.coerce.number().int().nonnegative().default(30000),\n  AI_CLI_ENABLE_HEARTBEAT: z.string().optional().default('true')\n});\n\n// Config exports pattern:\nexport const config = Object.freeze({\n  telegramBotToken: parsed.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN,\n  enableTelegram,\n  // ... all other config values\n  commandBlacklist: parseCsvList(parsed.COMMAND_BLACKLIST),\n  highRiskKeywords: parseCsvList(parsed.HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS),\n  directExecMode: parseBoolean(parsed.DIRECT_EXEC_MODE),\n});\n```\n\n### src/bot/commands/registry.js\n```javascript\n/**\n * Register a command with its metadata and handler.\n * @param {CommandMeta} meta - Command metadata\n * @param {Function} handler - Command handler function\n */\nexport function registerCommand(meta, handler) {\n  if (!meta || !meta.name) {\n    throw new Error('Command meta must have a name');\n  }\n  const normalizedMeta = {\n    ...meta,\n    name: meta.name.toLowerCase()\n  };\n  const name = normalizedMeta.name;\n  if (commands.has(name)) {\n    throw new Error(`Command \"${name}\" is already registered`);\n  }\n  commands.set(name, { meta: normalizedMeta, handler });\n  // Register aliases...\n}\n```\n\n### src/bot/commands/handlers/cd.js\n```javascript\n/**\n * CD command handler pattern\n */\nexport const cdMeta = {\n  name: 'cd',\n  aliases: [],\n  description: '切换工作目录',\n  usage: '/cd <路径>',\n  examples: ['/cd /tmp', '/cd ~', '/cd ..'],\n  params: [],\n  requiresAuth: true,\n  minRole: 'operator',\n  helpText: '/cd <路径> - 切换工作目录（不带参数显示当前目录）'\n};\n\nexport async function handleCd(handlerCtx) {\n  const { reply, sessionId, args = [] } = handlerCtx;\n  // Handler implementation...\n}\n```\n\n### src/security/permission-guard.js\n```javascript\nexport const ROLE_HIERARCHY = {\n  viewer: 0,\n  operator: 1,\n  admin: 2\n};\n\nconst COMMAND_MIN_ROLE = {\n  status: 'viewer',\n  logs: 'viewer',\n  // ... other commands\n  stop: 'admin',\n  reset: 'admin',\n  'force-unlock': 'admin',\n  exec: 'admin',\n};\n\nconst HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS = new Set(['stop', 'reset', 'force-unlock', 'commit-amend', 'commit-force']);\n\nexport function checkCommandPermission(userId, command) {\n  const userRole = getUserRole(userId);\n  const minRole = COMMAND_MIN_ROLE[command] || 'viewer';\n  // Role hierarchy check...\n  const requiresConfirmation = HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS.has(command);\n  return { allowed: true, requiresConfirmation };\n}\n```\n\n### src/services/session-store.js\n```javascript\nclass SessionStore {\n  #messagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #commitsBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #cwdBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #outputPagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #searchResultsBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #activeProcessBySessionKey = new Map();\n\n  get(sessionKey) { ... }\n  append(sessionKey, role, content) { ... }\n  clear(sessionKey) { ... }\n  getCwd(sessionKey) { ... }\n  setCwd(sessionKey, cwd) { ... }\n  // ... other methods\n}\n```\n\n### src/services/command-executor-service.js\n```javascript\nexport async function executeCommand(options) {\n  const { command, sessionId, userId, skipConfirmation = false, confirmationId } = options;\n\n  // Check blacklist first\n  const blacklistResult = checkCommandBlacklist(command, config.commandBlacklist);\n  if (blacklistResult.blocked) {\n    await logAuditEntry({...});\n    throw new Error(`命令被拒绝：${blacklistResult.reason}`);\n  }\n\n  // Detect high-risk keywords\n  const riskResult = detectHighRiskKeywords(command, config.highRiskKeywords);\n\n  // If high-risk and not confirmed, require confirmation\n  if (riskResult.isHighRisk && !skipConfirmation && !confirmationId) {\n    const params = { command, sessionId };\n    const { confirmId, message } = createConfirmation(userId, 'exec', params);\n    return {\n      needsConfirmation: true,\n      confirmationId: confirmId,\n      confirmationMessage: message,\n      detectedKeywords: riskResult.detectedKeywords\n    };\n  }\n  // ... execute command\n}\n```\n\n### src/bot/telegram.js (Command Registration Pattern)\n```javascript\nimport { registerCommand } from './commands/index.js';\n// Import handlers\nimport { cdMeta, handleCd } from './commands/handlers/cd.js';\n// ...\n\nfunction registerPipelineCommands() {\n  registerCommand(cdMeta, handleCd);\n  // ... other commands\n}\n\nexport function createTelegramBot() {\n  const bot = new Telegraf(config.telegramBotToken, {...});\n  registerPipelineCommands();\n  // ... bot setup\n}\n```\n\n### src/utils/markdown-v2-formatter.js\n```javascript\nexport function escapeMarkdownV2(text) {\n  if (!text) return '';\n  let result = text;\n  for (const char of ESCAPE_CHARS) {\n    result = result.split(char).join('\\\\' + char);\n  }\n  return result;\n}\n\nexport function formatCodeBlock(code, language = '') {...}\nexport function convertToMarkdownV2(markdown) {...}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 5 — Existing Tests\n\n### Test Pattern (tests/bot/commands/handlers/cd.test.js)\n```javascript\nimport { describe, test, beforeEach } from 'node:test';\nimport assert from 'node:assert/strict';\n\ndescribe('F-009 /cd Command Handler', () => {\n  let cdHandler;\n  let sessionStore;\n\n  beforeEach(async () => {\n    const projectRoot = process.cwd();\n    const cdModulePath = new URL(`file://${projectRoot}/src/bot/commands/handlers/cd.js`);\n    const module = await import(cdModulePath.href);\n    cdHandler = module;\n  });\n\n  describe('cdMeta', () => {\n    test('should export cdMeta with command metadata', async () => {\n      assert.ok(cdHandler.cdMeta);\n      assert.equal(cdHandler.cdMeta.name, 'cd');\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('handleCd', () => {\n    test('should update session cwd with valid directory', async () => {\n      const replies = [];\n      const handlerCtx = {\n        reply: (msg) => replies.push(msg),\n        sessionId: 'test-session',\n        args: ['/tmp']\n      };\n      await handleCd(handlerCtx);\n      // assertions...\n    });\n  });\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Key Design Decisions\n1. Use Node.js native `os` module and `child_process` for system info (no heavy dependencies)\n2. Store alert rules in JSON file under `data/` directory for persistence\n3. Use `setInterval` for monitoring checks, with configurable interval\n4. Format output as Markdown tables for Telegram display\n5. Integrate with existing permission system (F-006) for /kill command\n\n### File Structure to Create\n```\nsrc/\n├── services/\n│   ├── system-monitor-service.js    # Core monitoring logic\n│   └── alert-manager-service.js     # Alert rule management\n├── bot/commands/handlers/\n│   ├── sysinfo.js                   # /sysinfo command\n│   ├── ps.js                        # /ps command\n│   ├── kill.js                      # /kill command\n│   └── monitor.js                   # /monitor command\ndata/\n└── alert-rules.json                 # Persistent alert rules\ntests/\n├── services/\n│   ├── system-monitor-service.test.js\n│   └── alert-manager-service.test.js\n└── bot/commands/handlers/\n    ├── sysinfo.test.js\n    ├── ps.test.js\n    ├── kill.test.js\n    └── monitor.test.js\n```\n\n### Config Additions Needed\n```javascript\n// In config.js schema\nSYSTEM_MONITOR_INTERVAL_MS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(60000),\nSYSTEM_MONITOR_DATA_DIR: z.string().optional().default('data'),\n```\n","file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/012-system-monitor/context-snapshot.md"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":68913,"output_tokens":3221,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"__timestamp":"2026-03-12T20:30:42.716Z","_requestId":"0c0e04bf5f3f4ac585730d0e5b893431"}
