{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260313043121fb23b02420f648ef","session_id":"301af3e8-7399-4356-b525-ec1e2117384a","message":{"id":"20260313043121fb23b02420f648ef","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me continue with writing the plan.md file."}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"__timestamp":"2026-03-12T20:31:55.461Z","_requestId":"d34d194674fe4df2b045b65a2435281c"}
{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260313043121fb23b02420f648ef","session_id":"301af3e8-7399-4356-b525-ec1e2117384a","message":{"id":"20260313043121fb23b02420f648ef","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019ce3bf30e0f0e394b568d9341edd67","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# F-012: System Monitor - Implementation Plan\n\n## Overview\n\nSystem monitoring capability for PrizmClaw Telegram bot. Provides real-time system metrics, process management, and configurable alerting.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        Telegram Bot                              │\n│  /sysinfo  /ps  /kill  /monitor                                 │\n└───────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                │\n┌───────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Command Handlers                              │\n│  sysinfo.js │ ps.js │ kill.js │ monitor.js                      │\n└───────┬──────┴───────┴────────┴──────────────────────────────────┘\n        │\n┌───────▼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Service Layer                                  │\n│  ┌─────────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐           │\n│  │ SystemMonitorService│  │   AlertManagerService    │           │\n│  │ - getSystemInfo()   │  │ - addRule()              │           │\n│  │ - getProcessList()  │  │ - removeRule()           │           │\n│  │ - killProcess()     │  │ - checkThresholds()      │           │\n│  └─────────────────────┘  │ - loadRules()            │           │\n│                           │ - saveRules()            │           │\n│                           └──────────────────────────┘           │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n        │                           │\n        │                           ▼\n        │                  ┌───────────────────┐\n        │                  │ data/alert-rules  │\n        │                  │     .json         │\n        │                  └───────────────────┘\n        ▼\n┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Node.js Native APIs                            │\n│  os module │ child_process │ fs/promises                         │\n└───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Data Flow\n\n1. **System Info Flow**: `/sysinfo` → SystemMonitorService.getSystemInfo() → Format as table → Reply\n2. **Process List Flow**: `/ps` → SystemMonitorService.getProcessList() → Sort/Filter → Format → Reply\n3. **Kill Process Flow**: `/kill <pid>` → Permission Check → Confirmation → SystemMonitorService.killProcess() → Reply\n4. **Alert Flow**: `/monitor set cpu>80` → AlertManagerService.addRule() → Save to JSON → Interval Check → Push Alert\n\n## Interfaces\n\n### SystemMonitorService\n```javascript\ninterface SystemInfo {\n  cpu: {\n    usage: number;      // percentage 0-100\n    cores: number;\n    model: string;\n  };\n  memory: {\n    total: number;      // bytes\n    free: number;\n    used: number;\n    usagePercent: number;\n  };\n  disk: {\n    total: number;\n    free: number;\n    used: number;\n    usagePercent: number;\n  };\n  network: {\n    interfaces: string[];\n    bytesReceived: number;\n    bytesSent: number;\n  };\n  uptime: number;       // seconds\n  hostname: string;\n  platform: string;\n}\n\ninterface ProcessInfo {\n  pid: number;\n  name: string;\n  cpu: number;          // percentage\n  memory: number;       // percentage\n  memoryBytes: number;  // bytes\n  user: string;\n  command: string;\n}\n\nclass SystemMonitorService {\n  getSystemInfo(): Promise<SystemInfo>;\n  getProcessList(options?: { sortBy?: 'cpu'|'memory', filter?: string }): Promise<ProcessInfo[]>;\n  killProcess(pid: number, signal?: string): Promise<{ success: boolean, error?: string }>;\n}\n```\n\n### AlertManagerService\n```javascript\ninterface AlertRule {\n  id: string;\n  metric: 'cpu' | 'memory' | 'disk';\n  operator: '>' | '<' | '>=' | '<=';\n  threshold: number;\n  enabled: boolean;\n  createdAt: number;\n  lastTriggered?: number;\n}\n\ninterface AlertStatus {\n  ruleId: string;\n  metric: string;\n  currentValue: number;\n  threshold: number;\n  triggeredAt: number;\n}\n\nclass AlertManagerService {\n  addRule(rule: Omit<AlertRule, 'id' | 'createdAt'>): AlertRule;\n  removeRule(ruleId: string): boolean;\n  listRules(): AlertRule[];\n  enableRule(ruleId: string): boolean;\n  disableRule(ruleId: string): boolean;\n  checkThresholds(currentMetrics: SystemInfo): AlertStatus[];\n  startMonitoring(pushCallback: (alert: AlertStatus) => void): void;\n  stopMonitoring(): void;\n  loadRules(): Promise<void>;\n  saveRules(): Promise<void>;\n}\n```\n\n## Files to Create/Modify\n\n### New Files\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `src/services/system-monitor-service.js` | Core system monitoring functionality |\n| `src/services/alert-manager-service.js` | Alert rule management and monitoring loop |\n| `src/bot/commands/handlers/sysinfo.js` | `/sysinfo` command handler |\n| `src/bot/commands/handlers/ps.js` | `/ps` command handler |\n| `src/bot/commands/handlers/kill.js` | `/kill` command handler |\n| `src/bot/commands/handlers/monitor.js` | `/monitor` command handler |\n| `tests/services/system-monitor-service.test.js` | Unit tests for monitor service |\n| `tests/services/alert-manager-service.test.js` | Unit tests for alert manager |\n| `tests/bot/commands/handlers/sysinfo.test.js` | Tests for sysinfo handler |\n| `tests/bot/commands/handlers/ps.test.js` | Tests for ps handler |\n| `tests/bot/commands/handlers/kill.test.js` | Tests for kill handler |\n| `tests/bot/commands/handlers/monitor.test.js` | Tests for monitor handler |\n\n### Files to Modify\n| File | Changes |\n|------|---------|\n| `src/config.js` | Add SYSTEM_MONITOR_INTERVAL_MS, SYSTEM_MONITOR_DATA_DIR config options |\n| `src/bot/telegram.js` | Import and register new command handlers |\n| `src/security/permission-guard.js` | Add `kill` to COMMAND_MIN_ROLE and HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS |\n| `.prizm-docs/runtime.prizm` | Document new commands and TRAPS |\n| `.prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm` | Document new services |\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### 1. System Info Collection\n\nUse Node.js `os` module:\n- `os.cpus()` - CPU info and usage calculation\n- `os.totalmem()`, `os.freemem()` - Memory info\n- `os.uptime()` - System uptime\n- `os.hostname()`, `os.platform()` - System info\n- `os.networkInterfaces()` - Network interfaces\n\nDisk usage: Use `df` command (Unix) or `wmic` (Windows) via child_process\n\n### 2. Process List\n\nUse platform-specific commands:\n- macOS/Linux: `ps aux --sort=-%cpu` or `ps aux --sort=-%mem`\n- Parse output and filter/sort in JavaScript\n\n### 3. Kill Process\n\nUse `process.kill(pid, signal)` or `child_process.spawn('kill', [pid])`\n- Requires admin permission (F-006 integration)\n- Confirmation flow for safety\n\n### 4. Alert Monitoring\n\n- Store rules in `data/alert-rules.json`\n- Use `setInterval` to check thresholds periodically\n- Push alerts via Telegram bot when threshold exceeded\n- Cooldown period to prevent spam (e.g., 5 minutes between same alerts)\n\n### 5. Output Formatting\n\nFormat as Markdown tables for Telegram:\n```\n┌─────────┬──────────┐\n│ Metric  │ Value    │\n├─────────┼──────────┤\n│ CPU     │ 45.2%    │\n│ Memory  │ 62.8%    │\n│ Disk    │ 78.3%    │\n└─────────┴──────────┘\n```\n\nUse Telegram MarkdownV2 escaping for special characters.\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n- Mock `os` module and `child_process` for deterministic testing\n- Test alert rule CRUD operations\n- Test threshold detection logic\n- Test output formatting\n\n### Integration Tests\n- Test command handlers with mock Telegram context\n- Test alert persistence (load/save rules)\n- Test permission and confirmation flows\n\n### Test Coverage Goals\n- Services: 80%+ coverage\n- Handlers: 80%+ coverage\n- All acceptance criteria covered\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Permission Checks**: `/kill` requires admin role\n2. **Confirmation Flow**: `/kill` requires explicit confirmation\n3. **Rate Limiting**: Alert notifications have cooldown\n4. **Audit Logging**: All actions logged via audit-log-service\n5. **Input Validation**: PID must be numeric, metric names validated\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- No new npm dependencies required\n- Uses Node.js built-in: `os`, `child_process`, `fs/promises`\n- Integrates with existing: permission-guard, confirmation-manager, audit-log-service\n\n## Performance Considerations\n\n1. **Process List**: Can be slow with many processes - limit to top N\n2. **Monitoring Interval**: Default 60 seconds, configurable\n3. **Alert Cooldown**: Prevent notification spam\n4. **Memory Efficiency**: Don't store historical data, only current metrics\n","file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/012-system-monitor/plan.md"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":72233,"output_tokens":2130,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"__timestamp":"2026-03-12T20:31:55.468Z","_requestId":"d34d194674fe4df2b045b65a2435281c"}
