{"type":"assistant","uuid":"2026031304315545e9b82a92d64d62","session_id":"301af3e8-7399-4356-b525-ec1e2117384a","message":{"id":"2026031304315545e9b82a92d64d62","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019ce3bfb67c11b14093479af9fb3b39","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# F-012: System Monitor - Tasks\n\n## Phase 1: Core Services\n\n### T-1.1: Create SystemMonitorService\n- [ ] Create `src/services/system-monitor-service.js`\n- [ ] Implement `getSystemInfo()` using `os` module\n- [ ] Implement `getProcessList()` using `ps` command\n- [ ] Implement `killProcess()` using `process.kill()`\n- [ ] Add error handling for cross-platform compatibility\n\n### T-1.2: Create AlertManagerService\n- [ ] Create `src/services/alert-manager-service.js`\n- [ ] Implement rule CRUD: `addRule()`, `removeRule()`, `listRules()`\n- [ ] Implement rule persistence: `loadRules()`, `saveRules()`\n- [ ] Implement threshold checking: `checkThresholds()`\n- [ ] Implement monitoring loop: `startMonitoring()`, `stopMonitoring()`\n- [ ] Add cooldown mechanism to prevent spam\n\n### T-1.3: Add Config Options\n- [ ] Add `SYSTEM_MONITOR_INTERVAL_MS` to config schema\n- [ ] Add `SYSTEM_MONITOR_DATA_DIR` to config schema\n- [ ] Export new config values\n\n## Phase 2: Command Handlers\n\n### T-2.1: Create /sysinfo Handler\n- [ ] Create `src/bot/commands/handlers/sysinfo.js`\n- [ ] Define command metadata (name, description, minRole: viewer)\n- [ ] Implement handler calling SystemMonitorService.getSystemInfo()\n- [ ] Format output as Markdown table\n- [ ] Register command in telegram.js\n\n### T-2.2: Create /ps Handler\n- [ ] Create `src/bot/commands/handlers/ps.js`\n- [ ] Define command metadata (name, description, minRole: viewer)\n- [ ] Support `--sort=cpu|memory` option\n- [ ] Support `--filter=<keyword>` option\n- [ ] Implement pagination for large process lists\n- [ ] Register command in telegram.js\n\n### T-2.3: Create /kill Handler\n- [ ] Create `src/bot/commands/handlers/kill.js`\n- [ ] Define command metadata (name, description, minRole: admin)\n- [ ] Add to HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS requiring confirmation\n- [ ] Implement confirmation flow integration\n- [ ] Add audit logging for kill actions\n- [ ] Register command in telegram.js\n\n### T-2.4: Create /monitor Handler\n- [ ] Create `src/bot/commands/handlers/monitor.js`\n- [ ] Define command metadata with subcommands\n- [ ] Implement `set` subcommand: `/monitor set cpu>80`\n- [ ] Implement `list` subcommand: `/monitor list`\n- [ ] Implement `remove` subcommand: `/monitor remove <id>`\n- [ ] Implement `enable/disable` subcommands\n- [ ] Register command in telegram.js\n\n## Phase 3: Permission & Security\n\n### T-3.1: Update Permission Guard\n- [ ] Add `kill` to `COMMAND_MIN_ROLE` with 'admin' role\n- [ ] Add `kill` to `HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS` set\n- [ ] Add `sysinfo`, `ps`, `monitor` to `COMMAND_MIN_ROLE`\n\n## Phase 4: Tests\n\n### T-4.1: SystemMonitorService Tests\n- [ ] Create `tests/services/system-monitor-service.test.js`\n- [ ] Test `getSystemInfo()` returns valid structure\n- [ ] Test `getProcessList()` with sorting and filtering\n- [ ] Test `killProcess()` error handling\n- [ ] Test cross-platform compatibility (mock platform checks)\n\n### T-4.2: AlertManagerService Tests\n- [ ] Create `tests/services/alert-manager-service.test.js`\n- [ ] Test rule CRUD operations\n- [ ] Test persistence (save/load)\n- [ ] Test threshold detection logic\n- [ ] Test monitoring start/stop\n- [ ] Test cooldown mechanism\n\n### T-4.3: Command Handler Tests\n- [ ] Create `tests/bot/commands/handlers/sysinfo.test.js`\n- [ ] Create `tests/bot/commands/handlers/ps.test.js`\n- [ ] Create `tests/bot/commands/handlers/kill.test.js`\n- [ ] Create `tests/bot/commands/handlers/monitor.test.js`\n- [ ] Test metadata, handler function, output formatting\n\n### T-4.4: Integration Tests\n- [ ] Create `tests/integration/f012-system-monitor.test.js`\n- [ ] Test full command flow from Telegram to response\n- [ ] Test permission enforcement\n- [ ] Test confirmation flow for /kill\n\n## Phase 5: Documentation & Finalization\n\n### T-5.1: Update Prizm Docs\n- [ ] Update `.prizm-docs/runtime.prizm` with new commands\n- [ ] Update `.prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm` with new services\n- [ ] Add TRAPS for monitoring and process management\n\n### T-5.2: Create Data Directory\n- [ ] Create `data/` directory if not exists\n- [ ] Create initial empty `data/alert-rules.json`\n- [ ] Add `.gitkeep` to data directory\n\n### T-5.3: Final Verification\n- [ ] Run all tests: `npm test`\n- [ ] Manual test all commands in Telegram\n- [ ] Verify alert notifications work correctly\n- [ ] Check persistence after bot restart\n\n---\n\n## Task Dependencies\n\n```\nT-1.1 ─┬─► T-2.1 ─► T-4.3 (sysinfo)\n       ├─► T-2.2 ─► T-4.3 (ps)\n       └─► T-2.3 ─► T-4.3 (kill)\n              ▲\nT-3.1 ────────┘\n\nT-1.2 ─► T-2.4 ─► T-4.3 (monitor)\n   │\n   └─► T-4.2\n\nT-1.3 ─► T-1.2\n\nT-4.1, T-4.2, T-4.3 ─► T-4.4 ─► T-5.3\n```\n\n## Notes\n\n- TDD approach: Write tests first, then implementation\n- Each task should be completable in one session\n- Mark tasks `[x]` immediately after completion\n- Update context-snapshot.md with Implementation Log when done\n","file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/012-system-monitor/tasks.md"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":74405,"output_tokens":1424,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"__timestamp":"2026-03-12T20:32:19.716Z","_requestId":"d34d194674fe4df2b045b65a2435281c"}
