{"type":"user","uuid":"a079fa6d-d978-432d-9160-d31ddf589024","session_id":"301af3e8-7399-4356-b525-ec1e2117384a","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019ce3c027fd69a6094068e0053b123b","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→---\n   2→name: prizm-dev-team-dev\n   3→description: PrizmKit-integrated module implementer (multi-instance). Follows prizmkit.implement workflow with TDD, marks tasks [x] in tasks.md, works within assigned Git worktrees. Use when implementing specific feature modules.\n   4→tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, TaskCreate, TaskGet, TaskUpdate, TaskList, SendMessage\n   5→model: inherit\n   6→skills: prizmkit-implement, prizmkit-prizm-docs\n   7→---\n   8→\n   9→你是 **Dev Agent**，PrizmKit-integrated Multi-Agent 软件开发协作团队的模块实现者。\n  10→\n  11→### 核心身份\n  12→\n  13→你是团队的\"建筑工人\"——严格按图纸施工，使用 PrizmKit 的 implement 工作流作为执行引擎，专注于：\n  14→- 按照 tasks.md 和 plan.md 中的接口设计逐任务实现功能模块\n  15→- 遵循 TDD 方式开发（测试先行）\n  16→- 完成后立即标记 tasks.md 中的 `[x]`\n  17→- 产出代码和单元测试\n  18→\n  19→### 项目上下文\n  20→\n  21→项目文档在 `.prizm-docs/`。实现前先读 `root.prizm` 了解规则和已知陷阱（TRAPS），修改某模块时读该模块的文档。\n  22→\n  23→### 制品路径\n  24→\n  25→| 路径 | 用途 |\n  26→|------|------|\n  27→| `.prizm-docs/` | 项目知识层 — 规则、模式、已知陷阱 |\n  28→| `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/` | 功能制品 — spec.md / plan.md / tasks.md |\n  29→\n  30→### 必须做 (MUST)\n  31→\n  32→1. 按照分配的任务和 plan.md 中的接口设计实现功能模块\n  33→2. 遵循 TDD 方式：先写测试，再实现，再验证\n  34→3. 产出的代码必须通过本模块的单元测试\n  35→4. 发现接口设计歧义时，立即通过 Coordinator 上报 PM（不自行假设）\n  36→5. 遵循 `prizmkit.implement` 工作流：读取 tasks.md + plan.md + spec.md，逐任务实现\n  37→6. 每个任务完成后**立即**标记 tasks.md 中的 `[x]`（不批量标记）\n  38→7. 实现前读取 `.prizm-docs/` TRAPS 段避免已知陷阱\n  39→8. 检查点任务须验证构建通过和测试通过后才能继续下一阶段\n  40→9. 顺序任务按序执行，失败则停止；并行 `[P]` 任务可继续\n  41→10. 新建子模块时，生成对应的 `.prizm-docs/` L2 文档\n  42→\n  43→### 绝不做 (NEVER)\n  44→\n  45→- 不修改 plan.md 中的接口设计（修改需通过 PM）\n  46→- 不修改其他 Dev Agent 负责的模块代码\n  47→- 不进行集成测试（Reviewer 的职责）\n  48→- **不执行任何 git 操作**（git commit / git add / git reset / git push 均禁止 — 由 Orchestrator 通过 prizmkit.committer 统一提交）\n  49→- 不修改 `.prizmkit/specs/` 中除 `tasks.md`（标记 [x]）以外的任何文件\n  50→- 不为 bug 修复创建新的文档条目；bug 修复是现有功能的完善，应更新原始功能的文档而非在 REGISTRY.md 中创建新条目\n  51→- 不使用 TaskCreate/TaskUpdate 创建或修改 Orchestrator 层的任务（Task 工具仅用于内部进度追踪，且任务 ID 在各 agent 子会话中互不共享）\n  52→\n  53→### 行为规则\n  54→\n  55→```\n  56→DEV-01: 实现必须严格符合 plan.md 中定义的接口设计\n  57→DEV-02: 每个公开 API/函数必须有对应的单元测试\n  58→DEV-03: 发现接口设计歧义时，不得自行假设，必须上报\n  59→DEV-04: 任务完成后必须运行全部本模块测试\n  60→DEV-05: 代码提交信息遵循 Conventional Commits 格式（仅供参考，实际提交由 Orchestrator 执行）\n  61→DEV-06: 不得引入未在任务描述中声明的外部依赖\n  62→DEV-07: 遵循 prizmkit.implement 工作流\n  63→DEV-08: 每个任务完成后立即标记 tasks.md [x]\n  64→DEV-09: TDD：先写测试 → 再实现 → 再验证\n  65→DEV-10: 实现每个模块前必须读取 .prizm-docs/ TRAPS 段\n  66→DEV-11: 检查点任务必须验证构建通过和测试通过\n  67→DEV-12: 新建子模块时生成 L2 .prizm-docs/ 文档\n  68→DEV-13: 禁止执行任何 git 命令（git add/commit/reset/push 全部禁止）\n  69→DEV-14: 若 `npm test` 中存在 pre-existing 失败，不得忽略——必须在 COMPLETION_SIGNAL 中明确列出，由 Orchestrator 决策\n  70→```\n  71→\n  72→### 工作流程\n  73→\n  74→1. 接收任务分配\n  75→2. 读取 `.prizm-docs/root.prizm` 和相关模块文档\n  76→3. 读取 `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/` 中的 `tasks.md`、`plan.md`、`spec.md`\n  77→4. 对每个分配的任务，按 tasks.md 顺序执行：\n  78→   a. 读取目标文件模块的文档（检查 TRAPS 和 DECISIONS）\n  79→   b. TDD：基于验收标准编写测试 → 实现功能代码 → 运行测试验证\n  80→   c. 在 tasks.md 中标记该任务为 `[x]`\n  81→   d. 发送 STATUS_UPDATE 给 Coordinator\n  82→5. 如遇检查点任务，验证构建通过和测试通过后才继续\n  83→6. 遇到接口设计歧义，发送 ESCALATION（不自行假设）\n  84→7. 如新建了子模块，生成对应 `.prizm-docs/` L2 文档\n  85→8. 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL\n  86→\n  87→### 异常处理\n  88→\n  89→| 场景 | 策略 |\n  90→|------|------|\n  91→| 接口设计歧义 | 标记 BLOCKED → ESCALATION → 等待 PM 裁定 |\n  92→| 单元测试失败 | 最多重试修复 3 次 → 仍失败则 ISSUE_REPORT |\n  93→| 外部依赖不可用 | 使用 Mock → 标注说明 |\n  94→| 任务超出预估 | ESCALATION → 建议 PM 拆分任务 |\n  95→\n  96→### 通信规则\n  97→\n  98→允许 Agent 之间直接通信，但关键消息和结论必须通知 Coordinator。\n  99→- 发送 STATUS_UPDATE 汇报每个子任务完成\n 100→- 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL 标志所有任务完成\n 101→- 发送 ESCALATION 上报接口歧义或任务阻塞\n 102→- 接收 TASK_ASSIGNMENT 获取分配的工作\n 103→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce3c0133387a67221a0dc484f071a","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T20:32:29.791Z","_requestId":"d34d194674fe4df2b045b65a2435281c"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"9ba5c0b6-5bb5-410f-9ffa-79c6ca77276b","session_id":"301af3e8-7399-4356-b525-ec1e2117384a","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019ce3c02a30f8bfabe8eaffe5820e95","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-012: System Monitor - Context Snapshot\n   2→\n   3→## Section 1 — Feature Brief\n   4→\n   5→### Description\n   6→系统信息查看与监控能力，让用户随时了解电脑的运行状态。通过 Telegram 命令获取 CPU、内存、磁盘、网络等系统指标，查看进程列表，管理进程生命周期。\n   7→\n   8→### Commands Design\n   9→- `/sysinfo` - 返回系统概览（CPU 使用率、内存占用、磁盘空间、系统运行时间、网络状态）\n  10→- `/ps` - 返回进程列表支持按 CPU/内存排序和过滤\n  11→- `/kill <pid>` - 终止进程（需权限确认，集成 F-006）\n  12→- `/monitor set cpu>80` - 设置阈值告警，超过阈值时自动推送通知到 Telegram\n  13→\n  14→### Acceptance Criteria\n  15→1. `/sysinfo` 返回 CPU、内存、磁盘、网络的当前状态摘要，格式化为可读表格\n  16→2. `/ps` 返回进程列表，支持按 CPU/内存排序，支持过滤关键词\n  17→3. `/kill` 可终止指定进程，执行前需权限确认（集成 F-006 权限系统）\n  18→4. 支持设置监控阈值（如 CPU>80%），超过阈值时自动推送告警到 Telegram\n  19→5. 告警规则持久化存储，Bot 重启后自动恢复监控\n  20→6. 系统信息展示适配 Telegram 消息格式，信息密度高且可读性好\n  21→\n  22→### Dependencies\n  23→- F-009 - General Command Executor (completed)\n  24→\n  25→---\n  26→\n  27→## Section 2 — Project Structure\n  28→\n  29→```\n  30→src/\n  31→├── adapters/\n  32→├── bot/\n  33→│   ├── commands/\n  34→│   │   ├── handlers/      # Command handlers\n  35→│   │   ├── parser.js\n  36→│   │   ├── registry.js\n  37→│   │   ├── validator.js\n  38→│   │   └── index.js\n  39→│   └── telegram.js\n  40→├── config.js\n  41→├── http/\n  42→├── pipeline-infra/\n  43→├── routes/\n  44→├── security/\n  45→│   ├── permission-guard.js\n  46→│   ├── confirmation-manager.js\n  47→│   └── system-guard.js\n  48→├── services/\n  49→│   ├── session-store.js\n  50→│   ├── command-executor-service.js\n  51→│   └── ...\n  52→└── utils/\n  53→    ├── markdown-v2-formatter.js\n  54→    └── ...\n  55→tests/\n  56→├── bot/commands/handlers/\n  57→├── services/\n  58→├── security/\n  59→└── ...\n  60→```\n  61→\n  62→---\n  63→\n  64→## Section 3 — Prizm Context\n  65→\n  66→### root.prizm (L0)\n  67→```prizm\n  68→DOC_LEVEL: L0\n  69→PROJECT_NAME: PrizmClaw\n  70→PROJECT_TYPE: telegram-bridge + web-api\n  71→ADOPTION_MODE: brownfield\n  72→PLATFORM: codebuddy\n  73→LANGUAGES: JavaScript(ESM), HTML, CSS, Python, Shell\n  74→PACKAGE_MANAGER: npm\n  75→ENTRYPOINTS: src/index.js -> src/http/server.js + src/bot/telegram.js\n  76→```\n  77→\n  78→### runtime.prizm (L1) - Relevant Excerpts\n  79→```prizm\n  80→INTERFACES:\n  81→- Telegram: /start, /help, /reset, /screenshot, /exec, /cd, /more, /ls, /tree, /cat, /head, /tail, /find, /upload, /download, text message relay\n  82→- Security: PermissionGuard, ParamSanitizer, ConfirmationManager, AuditLogService, SystemGuard\n  83→\n  84→TRAPS:\n  85→- F-009: high-risk command keywords trigger confirmation flow (rm -rf, sudo, etc.)\n  86→- F-009: blacklist commands are rejected before execution\n  87→- permission check happens before command handler execution\n  88→```\n  89→\n  90→### security.prizm (L2) - Key Interfaces\n  91→```prizm\n  92→INTERFACES:\n  93→- getUserRole(userId) -> 'admin' | 'operator' | 'viewer'\n  94→- checkCommandPermission(userId, command) -> { allowed, requiresConfirmation, reason }\n  95→- isAdmin(userId) -> boolean\n  96→- createConfirmation(userId, action, params, timeoutMs) -> { confirmId, message }\n  97→- confirmAction(confirmId, userId) -> { ok, action?, params?, error? }\n  98→- logAuditEntry(entry) -> Promise<void>\n  99→\n 100→ROLE_HIERARCHY:\n 101→- viewer: 0 -> can view status and logs\n 102→- operator: 1 -> can run pipelines and retry\n 103→- admin: 2 -> can stop, reset, force-unlock, exec\n 104→\n 105→COMMAND_PERMISSIONS:\n 106→- status, logs, more, ls, tree, cat, head, tail, find: viewer\n 107→- pipeline, bugfix, planner, retry, cd, upload, download: operator\n 108→- stop, reset, force-unlock, exec: admin\n 109→```\n 110→\n 111→### services.prizm (L2) - Patterns\n 112→```prizm\n 113→PUBLIC_APIS:\n 114→- command executor (F-009): executeCommand/confirmHighRiskCommand -> blacklist check, high-risk detection, confirmation flow, cwd support, output pagination\n 115→- output pager (F-009): paginateOutput/storeOutputPages/getNextPage/clearPages/hasMorePages\n 116→\n 117→TRAPS:\n 118→- file-service validatePath checks against config.telegramFileAllowedRoots (frozen at startup)\n 119→```\n 120→\n 121→### bot.prizm (L2) - Command Registration Pattern\n 122→```prizm\n 123→INTERFACES:\n 124→- Telegram Commands:\n 125→  - /cd <path> - Change session working directory (F-009)\n 126→  - /more - View next page of paginated output (F-009)\n 127→\n 128→TRAPS:\n 129→- Commands require authorization via isAllowedUser()\n 130→- Command parsing normalizes to lowercase\n 131→- Registry stores normalized command names\n 132→```\n 133→\n 134→---\n 135→\n 136→## Section 4 — Existing Source Files\n 137→\n 138→### src/config.js\n 139→```javascript\n 140→import 'dotenv/config';\n 141→import { z } from 'zod';\n 142→\n 143→import { loadPipelineInfraConfig } from './pipeline-infra/config-loader.js';\n 144→import { resolveDaemonLogPaths } from './pipeline-infra/path-policy.js';\n 145→\n 146→const schema = z.object({\n 147→  TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN: z.string().optional().default(''),\n 148→  ENABLE_TELEGRAM: z.string().optional().default('true'),\n 149→  // ... other config options\n 150→  // F-009: General Command Executor\n 151→  COMMAND_BLACKLIST: z.string().optional().default(''),\n 152→  HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS: z.string().optional().default('rm -rf,sudo,kill,chmod -R,chown,dd,mkfs,shutdown,reboot,halt'),\n 153→  DIRECT_EXEC_MODE: z.string().optional().default('false'),\n 154→  // F-011: AI CLI Proxy\n 155→  AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_THRESHOLD_MS: z.coerce.number().int().nonnegative().default(10000),\n 156→  AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_MS: z.coerce.number().int().nonnegative().default(30000),\n 157→  AI_CLI_ENABLE_HEARTBEAT: z.string().optional().default('true')\n 158→});\n 159→\n 160→// Config exports pattern:\n 161→export const config = Object.freeze({\n 162→  telegramBotToken: parsed.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN,\n 163→  enableTelegram,\n 164→  // ... all other config values\n 165→  commandBlacklist: parseCsvList(parsed.COMMAND_BLACKLIST),\n 166→  highRiskKeywords: parseCsvList(parsed.HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS),\n 167→  directExecMode: parseBoolean(parsed.DIRECT_EXEC_MODE),\n 168→});\n 169→```\n 170→\n 171→### src/bot/commands/registry.js\n 172→```javascript\n 173→/**\n 174→ * Register a command with its metadata and handler.\n 175→ * @param {CommandMeta} meta - Command metadata\n 176→ * @param {Function} handler - Command handler function\n 177→ */\n 178→export function registerCommand(meta, handler) {\n 179→  if (!meta || !meta.name) {\n 180→    throw new Error('Command meta must have a name');\n 181→  }\n 182→  const normalizedMeta = {\n 183→    ...meta,\n 184→    name: meta.name.toLowerCase()\n 185→  };\n 186→  const name = normalizedMeta.name;\n 187→  if (commands.has(name)) {\n 188→    throw new Error(`Command \"${name}\" is already registered`);\n 189→  }\n 190→  commands.set(name, { meta: normalizedMeta, handler });\n 191→  // Register aliases...\n 192→}\n 193→```\n 194→\n 195→### src/bot/commands/handlers/cd.js\n 196→```javascript\n 197→/**\n 198→ * CD command handler pattern\n 199→ */\n 200→export const cdMeta = {\n 201→  name: 'cd',\n 202→  aliases: [],\n 203→  description: '切换工作目录',\n 204→  usage: '/cd <路径>',\n 205→  examples: ['/cd /tmp', '/cd ~', '/cd ..'],\n 206→  params: [],\n 207→  requiresAuth: true,\n 208→  minRole: 'operator',\n 209→  helpText: '/cd <路径> - 切换工作目录（不带参数显示当前目录）'\n 210→};\n 211→\n 212→export async function handleCd(handlerCtx) {\n 213→  const { reply, sessionId, args = [] } = handlerCtx;\n 214→  // Handler implementation...\n 215→}\n 216→```\n 217→\n 218→### src/security/permission-guard.js\n 219→```javascript\n 220→export const ROLE_HIERARCHY = {\n 221→  viewer: 0,\n 222→  operator: 1,\n 223→  admin: 2\n 224→};\n 225→\n 226→const COMMAND_MIN_ROLE = {\n 227→  status: 'viewer',\n 228→  logs: 'viewer',\n 229→  // ... other commands\n 230→  stop: 'admin',\n 231→  reset: 'admin',\n 232→  'force-unlock': 'admin',\n 233→  exec: 'admin',\n 234→};\n 235→\n 236→const HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS = new Set(['stop', 'reset', 'force-unlock', 'commit-amend', 'commit-force']);\n 237→\n 238→export function checkCommandPermission(userId, command) {\n 239→  const userRole = getUserRole(userId);\n 240→  const minRole = COMMAND_MIN_ROLE[command] || 'viewer';\n 241→  // Role hierarchy check...\n 242→  const requiresConfirmation = HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS.has(command);\n 243→  return { allowed: true, requiresConfirmation };\n 244→}\n 245→```\n 246→\n 247→### src/services/session-store.js\n 248→```javascript\n 249→class SessionStore {\n 250→  #messagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n 251→  #commitsBySessionKey = new Map();\n 252→  #cwdBySessionKey = new Map();\n 253→  #outputPagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n 254→  #searchResultsBySessionKey = new Map();\n 255→  #activeProcessBySessionKey = new Map();\n 256→\n 257→  get(sessionKey) { ... }\n 258→  append(sessionKey, role, content) { ... }\n 259→  clear(sessionKey) { ... }\n 260→  getCwd(sessionKey) { ... }\n 261→  setCwd(sessionKey, cwd) { ... }\n 262→  // ... other methods\n 263→}\n 264→```\n 265→\n 266→### src/services/command-executor-service.js\n 267→```javascript\n 268→export async function executeCommand(options) {\n 269→  const { command, sessionId, userId, skipConfirmation = false, confirmationId } = options;\n 270→\n 271→  // Check blacklist first\n 272→  const blacklistResult = checkCommandBlacklist(command, config.commandBlacklist);\n 273→  if (blacklistResult.blocked) {\n 274→    await logAuditEntry({...});\n 275→    throw new Error(`命令被拒绝：${blacklistResult.reason}`);\n 276→  }\n 277→\n 278→  // Detect high-risk keywords\n 279→  const riskResult = detectHighRiskKeywords(command, config.highRiskKeywords);\n 280→\n 281→  // If high-risk and not confirmed, require confirmation\n 282→  if (riskResult.isHighRisk && !skipConfirmation && !confirmationId) {\n 283→    const params = { command, sessionId };\n 284→    const { confirmId, message } = createConfirmation(userId, 'exec', params);\n 285→    return {\n 286→      needsConfirmation: true,\n 287→      confirmationId: confirmId,\n 288→      confirmationMessage: message,\n 289→      detectedKeywords: riskResult.detectedKeywords\n 290→    };\n 291→  }\n 292→  // ... execute command\n 293→}\n 294→```\n 295→\n 296→### src/bot/telegram.js (Command Registration Pattern)\n 297→```javascript\n 298→import { registerCommand } from './commands/index.js';\n 299→// Import handlers\n 300→import { cdMeta, handleCd } from './commands/handlers/cd.js';\n 301→// ...\n 302→\n 303→function registerPipelineCommands() {\n 304→  registerCommand(cdMeta, handleCd);\n 305→  // ... other commands\n 306→}\n 307→\n 308→export function createTelegramBot() {\n 309→  const bot = new Telegraf(config.telegramBotToken, {...});\n 310→  registerPipelineCommands();\n 311→  // ... bot setup\n 312→}\n 313→```\n 314→\n 315→### src/utils/markdown-v2-formatter.js\n 316→```javascript\n 317→export function escapeMarkdownV2(text) {\n 318→  if (!text) return '';\n 319→  let result = text;\n 320→  for (const char of ESCAPE_CHARS) {\n 321→    result = result.split(char).join('\\\\' + char);\n 322→  }\n 323→  return result;\n 324→}\n 325→\n 326→export function formatCodeBlock(code, language = '') {...}\n 327→export function convertToMarkdownV2(markdown) {...}\n 328→```\n 329→\n 330→---\n 331→\n 332→## Section 5 — Existing Tests\n 333→\n 334→### Test Pattern (tests/bot/commands/handlers/cd.test.js)\n 335→```javascript\n 336→import { describe, test, beforeEach } from 'node:test';\n 337→import assert from 'node:assert/strict';\n 338→\n 339→describe('F-009 /cd Command Handler', () => {\n 340→  let cdHandler;\n 341→  let sessionStore;\n 342→\n 343→  beforeEach(async () => {\n 344→    const projectRoot = process.cwd();\n 345→    const cdModulePath = new URL(`file://${projectRoot}/src/bot/commands/handlers/cd.js`);\n 346→    const module = await import(cdModulePath.href);\n 347→    cdHandler = module;\n 348→  });\n 349→\n 350→  describe('cdMeta', () => {\n 351→    test('should export cdMeta with command metadata', async () => {\n 352→      assert.ok(cdHandler.cdMeta);\n 353→      assert.equal(cdHandler.cdMeta.name, 'cd');\n 354→    });\n 355→  });\n 356→\n 357→  describe('handleCd', () => {\n 358→    test('should update session cwd with valid directory', async () => {\n 359→      const replies = [];\n 360→      const handlerCtx = {\n 361→        reply: (msg) => replies.push(msg),\n 362→        sessionId: 'test-session',\n 363→        args: ['/tmp']\n 364→      };\n 365→      await handleCd(handlerCtx);\n 366→      // assertions...\n 367→    });\n 368→  });\n 369→});\n 370→```\n 371→\n 372→---\n 373→\n 374→## Implementation Notes\n 375→\n 376→### Key Design Decisions\n 377→1. Use Node.js native `os` module and `child_process` for system info (no heavy dependencies)\n 378→2. Store alert rules in JSON file under `data/` directory for persistence\n 379→3. Use `setInterval` for monitoring checks, with configurable interval\n 380→4. Format output as Markdown tables for Telegram display\n 381→5. Integrate with existing permission system (F-006) for /kill command\n 382→\n 383→### File Structure to Create\n 384→```\n 385→src/\n 386→├── services/\n 387→│   ├── system-monitor-service.js    # Core monitoring logic\n 388→│   └── alert-manager-service.js     # Alert rule management\n 389→├── bot/commands/handlers/\n 390→│   ├── sysinfo.js                   # /sysinfo command\n 391→│   ├── ps.js                        # /ps command\n 392→│   ├── kill.js                      # /kill command\n 393→│   └── monitor.js                   # /monitor command\n 394→data/\n 395→└── alert-rules.json                 # Persistent alert rules\n 396→tests/\n 397→├── services/\n 398→│   ├── system-monitor-service.test.js\n 399→│   └── alert-manager-service.test.js\n 400→└── bot/commands/handlers/\n 401→    ├── sysinfo.test.js\n 402→    ├── ps.test.js\n 403→    ├── kill.test.js\n 404→    └── monitor.test.js\n 405→```\n 406→\n 407→### Config Additions Needed\n 408→```javascript\n 409→// In config.js schema\n 410→SYSTEM_MONITOR_INTERVAL_MS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(60000),\n 411→SYSTEM_MONITOR_DATA_DIR: z.string().optional().default('data'),\n 412→```\n 413→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce3c0133387a67221a0dc484f071a","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T20:32:29.792Z","_requestId":"d34d194674fe4df2b045b65a2435281c"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"361d4942-4cdc-4aa2-a80d-148f3a8322a4","session_id":"301af3e8-7399-4356-b525-ec1e2117384a","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019ce3c02c7a4ed2747d1eafa0d4616c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-012: System Monitor - Implementation Plan\n   2→\n   3→## Overview\n   4→\n   5→System monitoring capability for PrizmClaw Telegram bot. Provides real-time system metrics, process management, and configurable alerting.\n   6→\n   7→## Architecture\n   8→\n   9→### Components\n  10→\n  11→```\n  12→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  13→│                        Telegram Bot                              │\n  14→│  /sysinfo  /ps  /kill  /monitor                                 │\n  15→└───────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  16→                │\n  17→┌───────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  18→│                    Command Handlers                              │\n  19→│  sysinfo.js │ ps.js │ kill.js │ monitor.js                      │\n  20→└───────┬──────┴───────┴────────┴──────────────────────────────────┘\n  21→        │\n  22→┌───────▼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  23→│                    Service Layer                                  │\n  24→│  ┌─────────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐           │\n  25→│  │ SystemMonitorService│  │   AlertManagerService    │           │\n  26→│  │ - getSystemInfo()   │  │ - addRule()              │           │\n  27→│  │ - getProcessList()  │  │ - removeRule()           │           │\n  28→│  │ - killProcess()     │  │ - checkThresholds()      │           │\n  29→│  └─────────────────────┘  │ - loadRules()            │           │\n  30→│                           │ - saveRules()            │           │\n  31→│                           └──────────────────────────┘           │\n  32→└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  33→        │                           │\n  34→        │                           ▼\n  35→        │                  ┌───────────────────┐\n  36→        │                  │ data/alert-rules  │\n  37→        │                  │     .json         │\n  38→        │                  └───────────────────┘\n  39→        ▼\n  40→┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  41→│                    Node.js Native APIs                            │\n  42→│  os module │ child_process │ fs/promises                         │\n  43→└───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  44→```\n  45→\n  46→### Data Flow\n  47→\n  48→1. **System Info Flow**: `/sysinfo` → SystemMonitorService.getSystemInfo() → Format as table → Reply\n  49→2. **Process List Flow**: `/ps` → SystemMonitorService.getProcessList() → Sort/Filter → Format → Reply\n  50→3. **Kill Process Flow**: `/kill <pid>` → Permission Check → Confirmation → SystemMonitorService.killProcess() → Reply\n  51→4. **Alert Flow**: `/monitor set cpu>80` → AlertManagerService.addRule() → Save to JSON → Interval Check → Push Alert\n  52→\n  53→## Interfaces\n  54→\n  55→### SystemMonitorService\n  56→```javascript\n  57→interface SystemInfo {\n  58→  cpu: {\n  59→    usage: number;      // percentage 0-100\n  60→    cores: number;\n  61→    model: string;\n  62→  };\n  63→  memory: {\n  64→    total: number;      // bytes\n  65→    free: number;\n  66→    used: number;\n  67→    usagePercent: number;\n  68→  };\n  69→  disk: {\n  70→    total: number;\n  71→    free: number;\n  72→    used: number;\n  73→    usagePercent: number;\n  74→  };\n  75→  network: {\n  76→    interfaces: string[];\n  77→    bytesReceived: number;\n  78→    bytesSent: number;\n  79→  };\n  80→  uptime: number;       // seconds\n  81→  hostname: string;\n  82→  platform: string;\n  83→}\n  84→\n  85→interface ProcessInfo {\n  86→  pid: number;\n  87→  name: string;\n  88→  cpu: number;          // percentage\n  89→  memory: number;       // percentage\n  90→  memoryBytes: number;  // bytes\n  91→  user: string;\n  92→  command: string;\n  93→}\n  94→\n  95→class SystemMonitorService {\n  96→  getSystemInfo(): Promise<SystemInfo>;\n  97→  getProcessList(options?: { sortBy?: 'cpu'|'memory', filter?: string }): Promise<ProcessInfo[]>;\n  98→  killProcess(pid: number, signal?: string): Promise<{ success: boolean, error?: string }>;\n  99→}\n 100→```\n 101→\n 102→### AlertManagerService\n 103→```javascript\n 104→interface AlertRule {\n 105→  id: string;\n 106→  metric: 'cpu' | 'memory' | 'disk';\n 107→  operator: '>' | '<' | '>=' | '<=';\n 108→  threshold: number;\n 109→  enabled: boolean;\n 110→  createdAt: number;\n 111→  lastTriggered?: number;\n 112→}\n 113→\n 114→interface AlertStatus {\n 115→  ruleId: string;\n 116→  metric: string;\n 117→  currentValue: number;\n 118→  threshold: number;\n 119→  triggeredAt: number;\n 120→}\n 121→\n 122→class AlertManagerService {\n 123→  addRule(rule: Omit<AlertRule, 'id' | 'createdAt'>): AlertRule;\n 124→  removeRule(ruleId: string): boolean;\n 125→  listRules(): AlertRule[];\n 126→  enableRule(ruleId: string): boolean;\n 127→  disableRule(ruleId: string): boolean;\n 128→  checkThresholds(currentMetrics: SystemInfo): AlertStatus[];\n 129→  startMonitoring(pushCallback: (alert: AlertStatus) => void): void;\n 130→  stopMonitoring(): void;\n 131→  loadRules(): Promise<void>;\n 132→  saveRules(): Promise<void>;\n 133→}\n 134→```\n 135→\n 136→## Files to Create/Modify\n 137→\n 138→### New Files\n 139→| File | Purpose |\n 140→|------|---------|\n 141→| `src/services/system-monitor-service.js` | Core system monitoring functionality |\n 142→| `src/services/alert-manager-service.js` | Alert rule management and monitoring loop |\n 143→| `src/bot/commands/handlers/sysinfo.js` | `/sysinfo` command handler |\n 144→| `src/bot/commands/handlers/ps.js` | `/ps` command handler |\n 145→| `src/bot/commands/handlers/kill.js` | `/kill` command handler |\n 146→| `src/bot/commands/handlers/monitor.js` | `/monitor` command handler |\n 147→| `tests/services/system-monitor-service.test.js` | Unit tests for monitor service |\n 148→| `tests/services/alert-manager-service.test.js` | Unit tests for alert manager |\n 149→| `tests/bot/commands/handlers/sysinfo.test.js` | Tests for sysinfo handler |\n 150→| `tests/bot/commands/handlers/ps.test.js` | Tests for ps handler |\n 151→| `tests/bot/commands/handlers/kill.test.js` | Tests for kill handler |\n 152→| `tests/bot/commands/handlers/monitor.test.js` | Tests for monitor handler |\n 153→\n 154→### Files to Modify\n 155→| File | Changes |\n 156→|------|---------|\n 157→| `src/config.js` | Add SYSTEM_MONITOR_INTERVAL_MS, SYSTEM_MONITOR_DATA_DIR config options |\n 158→| `src/bot/telegram.js` | Import and register new command handlers |\n 159→| `src/security/permission-guard.js` | Add `kill` to COMMAND_MIN_ROLE and HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS |\n 160→| `.prizm-docs/runtime.prizm` | Document new commands and TRAPS |\n 161→| `.prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm` | Document new services |\n 162→\n 163→## Implementation Details\n 164→\n 165→### 1. System Info Collection\n 166→\n 167→Use Node.js `os` module:\n 168→- `os.cpus()` - CPU info and usage calculation\n 169→- `os.totalmem()`, `os.freemem()` - Memory info\n 170→- `os.uptime()` - System uptime\n 171→- `os.hostname()`, `os.platform()` - System info\n 172→- `os.networkInterfaces()` - Network interfaces\n 173→\n 174→Disk usage: Use `df` command (Unix) or `wmic` (Windows) via child_process\n 175→\n 176→### 2. Process List\n 177→\n 178→Use platform-specific commands:\n 179→- macOS/Linux: `ps aux --sort=-%cpu` or `ps aux --sort=-%mem`\n 180→- Parse output and filter/sort in JavaScript\n 181→\n 182→### 3. Kill Process\n 183→\n 184→Use `process.kill(pid, signal)` or `child_process.spawn('kill', [pid])`\n 185→- Requires admin permission (F-006 integration)\n 186→- Confirmation flow for safety\n 187→\n 188→### 4. Alert Monitoring\n 189→\n 190→- Store rules in `data/alert-rules.json`\n 191→- Use `setInterval` to check thresholds periodically\n 192→- Push alerts via Telegram bot when threshold exceeded\n 193→- Cooldown period to prevent spam (e.g., 5 minutes between same alerts)\n 194→\n 195→### 5. Output Formatting\n 196→\n 197→Format as Markdown tables for Telegram:\n 198→```\n 199→┌─────────┬──────────┐\n 200→│ Metric  │ Value    │\n 201→├─────────┼──────────┤\n 202→│ CPU     │ 45.2%    │\n 203→│ Memory  │ 62.8%    │\n 204→│ Disk    │ 78.3%    │\n 205→└─────────┴──────────┘\n 206→```\n 207→\n 208→Use Telegram MarkdownV2 escaping for special characters.\n 209→\n 210→## Testing Strategy\n 211→\n 212→### Unit Tests\n 213→- Mock `os` module and `child_process` for deterministic testing\n 214→- Test alert rule CRUD operations\n 215→- Test threshold detection logic\n 216→- Test output formatting\n 217→\n 218→### Integration Tests\n 219→- Test command handlers with mock Telegram context\n 220→- Test alert persistence (load/save rules)\n 221→- Test permission and confirmation flows\n 222→\n 223→### Test Coverage Goals\n 224→- Services: 80%+ coverage\n 225→- Handlers: 80%+ coverage\n 226→- All acceptance criteria covered\n 227→\n 228→## Security Considerations\n 229→\n 230→1. **Permission Checks**: `/kill` requires admin role\n 231→2. **Confirmation Flow**: `/kill` requires explicit confirmation\n 232→3. **Rate Limiting**: Alert notifications have cooldown\n 233→4. **Audit Logging**: All actions logged via audit-log-service\n 234→5. **Input Validation**: PID must be numeric, metric names validated\n 235→\n 236→## Dependencies\n 237→\n 238→- No new npm dependencies required\n 239→- Uses Node.js built-in: `os`, `child_process`, `fs/promises`\n 240→- Integrates with existing: permission-guard, confirmation-manager, audit-log-service\n 241→\n 242→## Performance Considerations\n 243→\n 244→1. **Process List**: Can be slow with many processes - limit to top N\n 245→2. **Monitoring Interval**: Default 60 seconds, configurable\n 246→3. **Alert Cooldown**: Prevent notification spam\n 247→4. **Memory Efficiency**: Don't store historical data, only current metrics\n 248→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce3c0133387a67221a0dc484f071a","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T20:32:29.792Z","_requestId":"d34d194674fe4df2b045b65a2435281c"}
