{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260313044443b148aa606daf4f46","session_id":"301af3e8-7399-4356-b525-ec1e2117384a","message":{"id":"20260313044443b148aa606daf4f46","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019ce3cb6abea3e6fb60e0946013bb09","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/012-system-monitor/context-snapshot.md"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":83543,"output_tokens":49,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce3c0133387a67221a0dc484f071a","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T20:44:45.737Z","_requestId":"d34d194674fe4df2b045b65a2435281c"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"2e7feb44-0a4d-46a1-ba36-59534979ef5e","session_id":"301af3e8-7399-4356-b525-ec1e2117384a","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019ce3cb6abea3e6fb60e0946013bb09","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-012: System Monitor - Context Snapshot\n   2→\n   3→## Section 1 — Feature Brief\n   4→\n   5→### Description\n   6→系统信息查看与监控能力，让用户随时了解电脑的运行状态。通过 Telegram 命令获取 CPU、内存、磁盘、网络等系统指标，查看进程列表，管理进程生命周期。\n   7→\n   8→### Commands Design\n   9→- `/sysinfo` - 返回系统概览（CPU 使用率、内存占用、磁盘空间、系统运行时间、网络状态）\n  10→- `/ps` - 返回进程列表支持按 CPU/内存排序和过滤\n  11→- `/kill <pid>` - 终止进程（需权限确认，集成 F-006）\n  12→- `/monitor set cpu>80` - 设置阈值告警，超过阈值时自动推送通知到 Telegram\n  13→\n  14→### Acceptance Criteria\n  15→1. `/sysinfo` 返回 CPU、内存、磁盘、网络的当前状态摘要，格式化为可读表格\n  16→2. `/ps` 返回进程列表，支持按 CPU/内存排序，支持过滤关键词\n  17→3. `/kill` 可终止指定进程，执行前需权限确认（集成 F-006 权限系统）\n  18→4. 支持设置监控阈值（如 CPU>80%），超过阈值时自动推送告警到 Telegram\n  19→5. 告警规则持久化存储，Bot 重启后自动恢复监控\n  20→6. 系统信息展示适配 Telegram 消息格式，信息密度高且可读性好\n  21→\n  22→### Dependencies\n  23→- F-009 - General Command Executor (completed)\n  24→\n  25→---\n  26→\n  27→## Section 2 — Project Structure\n  28→\n  29→```\n  30→src/\n  31→├── adapters/\n  32→├── bot/\n  33→│   ├── commands/\n  34→│   │   ├── handlers/      # Command handlers\n  35→│   │   ├── parser.js\n  36→│   │   ├── registry.js\n  37→│   │   ├── validator.js\n  38→│   │   └── index.js\n  39→│   └── telegram.js\n  40→├── config.js\n  41→├── http/\n  42→├── pipeline-infra/\n  43→├── routes/\n  44→├── security/\n  45→│   ├── permission-guard.js\n  46→│   ├── confirmation-manager.js\n  47→│   └── system-guard.js\n  48→├── services/\n  49→│   ├── session-store.js\n  50→│   ├── command-executor-service.js\n  51→│   └── ...\n  52→└── utils/\n  53→    ├── markdown-v2-formatter.js\n  54→    └── ...\n  55→tests/\n  56→├── bot/commands/handlers/\n  57→├── services/\n  58→├── security/\n  59→└── ...\n  60→```\n  61→\n  62→---\n  63→\n  64→## Section 3 — Prizm Context\n  65→\n  66→### root.prizm (L0)\n  67→```prizm\n  68→DOC_LEVEL: L0\n  69→PROJECT_NAME: PrizmClaw\n  70→PROJECT_TYPE: telegram-bridge + web-api\n  71→ADOPTION_MODE: brownfield\n  72→PLATFORM: codebuddy\n  73→LANGUAGES: JavaScript(ESM), HTML, CSS, Python, Shell\n  74→PACKAGE_MANAGER: npm\n  75→ENTRYPOINTS: src/index.js -> src/http/server.js + src/bot/telegram.js\n  76→```\n  77→\n  78→### runtime.prizm (L1) - Relevant Excerpts\n  79→```prizm\n  80→INTERFACES:\n  81→- Telegram: /start, /help, /reset, /screenshot, /exec, /cd, /more, /ls, /tree, /cat, /head, /tail, /find, /upload, /download, text message relay\n  82→- Security: PermissionGuard, ParamSanitizer, ConfirmationManager, AuditLogService, SystemGuard\n  83→\n  84→TRAPS:\n  85→- F-009: high-risk command keywords trigger confirmation flow (rm -rf, sudo, etc.)\n  86→- F-009: blacklist commands are rejected before execution\n  87→- permission check happens before command handler execution\n  88→```\n  89→\n  90→### security.prizm (L2) - Key Interfaces\n  91→```prizm\n  92→INTERFACES:\n  93→- getUserRole(userId) -> 'admin' | 'operator' | 'viewer'\n  94→- checkCommandPermission(userId, command) -> { allowed, requiresConfirmation, reason }\n  95→- isAdmin(userId) -> boolean\n  96→- createConfirmation(userId, action, params, timeoutMs) -> { confirmId, message }\n  97→- confirmAction(confirmId, userId) -> { ok, action?, params?, error? }\n  98→- logAuditEntry(entry) -> Promise<void>\n  99→\n 100→ROLE_HIERARCHY:\n 101→- viewer: 0 -> can view status and logs\n 102→- operator: 1 -> can run pipelines and retry\n 103→- admin: 2 -> can stop, reset, force-unlock, exec\n 104→\n 105→COMMAND_PERMISSIONS:\n 106→- status, logs, more, ls, tree, cat, head, tail, find: viewer\n 107→- pipeline, bugfix, planner, retry, cd, upload, download: operator\n 108→- stop, reset, force-unlock, exec: admin\n 109→```\n 110→\n 111→### services.prizm (L2) - Patterns\n 112→```prizm\n 113→PUBLIC_APIS:\n 114→- command executor (F-009): executeCommand/confirmHighRiskCommand -> blacklist check, high-risk detection, confirmation flow, cwd support, output pagination\n 115→- output pager (F-009): paginateOutput/storeOutputPages/getNextPage/clearPages/hasMorePages\n 116→\n 117→TRAPS:\n 118→- file-service validatePath checks against config.telegramFileAllowedRoots (frozen at startup)\n 119→```\n 120→\n 121→### bot.prizm (L2) - Command Registration Pattern\n 122→```prizm\n 123→INTERFACES:\n 124→- Telegram Commands:\n 125→  - /cd <path> - Change session working directory (F-009)\n 126→  - /more - View next page of paginated output (F-009)\n 127→\n 128→TRAPS:\n 129→- Commands require authorization via isAllowedUser()\n 130→- Command parsing normalizes to lowercase\n 131→- Registry stores normalized command names\n 132→```\n 133→\n 134→---\n 135→\n 136→## Section 4 — Existing Source Files\n 137→\n 138→### src/config.js\n 139→```javascript\n 140→import 'dotenv/config';\n 141→import { z } from 'zod';\n 142→\n 143→import { loadPipelineInfraConfig } from './pipeline-infra/config-loader.js';\n 144→import { resolveDaemonLogPaths } from './pipeline-infra/path-policy.js';\n 145→\n 146→const schema = z.object({\n 147→  TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN: z.string().optional().default(''),\n 148→  ENABLE_TELEGRAM: z.string().optional().default('true'),\n 149→  // ... other config options\n 150→  // F-009: General Command Executor\n 151→  COMMAND_BLACKLIST: z.string().optional().default(''),\n 152→  HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS: z.string().optional().default('rm -rf,sudo,kill,chmod -R,chown,dd,mkfs,shutdown,reboot,halt'),\n 153→  DIRECT_EXEC_MODE: z.string().optional().default('false'),\n 154→  // F-011: AI CLI Proxy\n 155→  AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_THRESHOLD_MS: z.coerce.number().int().nonnegative().default(10000),\n 156→  AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_MS: z.coerce.number().int().nonnegative().default(30000),\n 157→  AI_CLI_ENABLE_HEARTBEAT: z.string().optional().default('true')\n 158→});\n 159→\n 160→// Config exports pattern:\n 161→export const config = Object.freeze({\n 162→  telegramBotToken: parsed.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN,\n 163→  enableTelegram,\n 164→  // ... all other config values\n 165→  commandBlacklist: parseCsvList(parsed.COMMAND_BLACKLIST),\n 166→  highRiskKeywords: parseCsvList(parsed.HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS),\n 167→  directExecMode: parseBoolean(parsed.DIRECT_EXEC_MODE),\n 168→});\n 169→```\n 170→\n 171→### src/bot/commands/registry.js\n 172→```javascript\n 173→/**\n 174→ * Register a command with its metadata and handler.\n 175→ * @param {CommandMeta} meta - Command metadata\n 176→ * @param {Function} handler - Command handler function\n 177→ */\n 178→export function registerCommand(meta, handler) {\n 179→  if (!meta || !meta.name) {\n 180→    throw new Error('Command meta must have a name');\n 181→  }\n 182→  const normalizedMeta = {\n 183→    ...meta,\n 184→    name: meta.name.toLowerCase()\n 185→  };\n 186→  const name = normalizedMeta.name;\n 187→  if (commands.has(name)) {\n 188→    throw new Error(`Command \"${name}\" is already registered`);\n 189→  }\n 190→  commands.set(name, { meta: normalizedMeta, handler });\n 191→  // Register aliases...\n 192→}\n 193→```\n 194→\n 195→### src/bot/commands/handlers/cd.js\n 196→```javascript\n 197→/**\n 198→ * CD command handler pattern\n 199→ */\n 200→export const cdMeta = {\n 201→  name: 'cd',\n 202→  aliases: [],\n 203→  description: '切换工作目录',\n 204→  usage: '/cd <路径>',\n 205→  examples: ['/cd /tmp', '/cd ~', '/cd ..'],\n 206→  params: [],\n 207→  requiresAuth: true,\n 208→  minRole: 'operator',\n 209→  helpText: '/cd <路径> - 切换工作目录（不带参数显示当前目录）'\n 210→};\n 211→\n 212→export async function handleCd(handlerCtx) {\n 213→  const { reply, sessionId, args = [] } = handlerCtx;\n 214→  // Handler implementation...\n 215→}\n 216→```\n 217→\n 218→### src/security/permission-guard.js\n 219→```javascript\n 220→export const ROLE_HIERARCHY = {\n 221→  viewer: 0,\n 222→  operator: 1,\n 223→  admin: 2\n 224→};\n 225→\n 226→const COMMAND_MIN_ROLE = {\n 227→  status: 'viewer',\n 228→  logs: 'viewer',\n 229→  // ... other commands\n 230→  stop: 'admin',\n 231→  reset: 'admin',\n 232→  'force-unlock': 'admin',\n 233→  exec: 'admin',\n 234→};\n 235→\n 236→const HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS = new Set(['stop', 'reset', 'force-unlock', 'commit-amend', 'commit-force']);\n 237→\n 238→export function checkCommandPermission(userId, command) {\n 239→  const userRole = getUserRole(userId);\n 240→  const minRole = COMMAND_MIN_ROLE[command] || 'viewer';\n 241→  // Role hierarchy check...\n 242→  const requiresConfirmation = HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS.has(command);\n 243→  return { allowed: true, requiresConfirmation };\n 244→}\n 245→```\n 246→\n 247→### src/services/session-store.js\n 248→```javascript\n 249→class SessionStore {\n 250→  #messagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n 251→  #commitsBySessionKey = new Map();\n 252→  #cwdBySessionKey = new Map();\n 253→  #outputPagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n 254→  #searchResultsBySessionKey = new Map();\n 255→  #activeProcessBySessionKey = new Map();\n 256→\n 257→  get(sessionKey) { ... }\n 258→  append(sessionKey, role, content) { ... }\n 259→  clear(sessionKey) { ... }\n 260→  getCwd(sessionKey) { ... }\n 261→  setCwd(sessionKey, cwd) { ... }\n 262→  // ... other methods\n 263→}\n 264→```\n 265→\n 266→### src/services/command-executor-service.js\n 267→```javascript\n 268→export async function executeCommand(options) {\n 269→  const { command, sessionId, userId, skipConfirmation = false, confirmationId } = options;\n 270→\n 271→  // Check blacklist first\n 272→  const blacklistResult = checkCommandBlacklist(command, config.commandBlacklist);\n 273→  if (blacklistResult.blocked) {\n 274→    await logAuditEntry({...});\n 275→    throw new Error(`命令被拒绝：${blacklistResult.reason}`);\n 276→  }\n 277→\n 278→  // Detect high-risk keywords\n 279→  const riskResult = detectHighRiskKeywords(command, config.highRiskKeywords);\n 280→\n 281→  // If high-risk and not confirmed, require confirmation\n 282→  if (riskResult.isHighRisk && !skipConfirmation && !confirmationId) {\n 283→    const params = { command, sessionId };\n 284→    const { confirmId, message } = createConfirmation(userId, 'exec', params);\n 285→    return {\n 286→      needsConfirmation: true,\n 287→      confirmationId: confirmId,\n 288→      confirmationMessage: message,\n 289→      detectedKeywords: riskResult.detectedKeywords\n 290→    };\n 291→  }\n 292→  // ... execute command\n 293→}\n 294→```\n 295→\n 296→### src/bot/telegram.js (Command Registration Pattern)\n 297→```javascript\n 298→import { registerCommand } from './commands/index.js';\n 299→// Import handlers\n 300→import { cdMeta, handleCd } from './commands/handlers/cd.js';\n 301→// ...\n 302→\n 303→function registerPipelineCommands() {\n 304→  registerCommand(cdMeta, handleCd);\n 305→  // ... other commands\n 306→}\n 307→\n 308→export function createTelegramBot() {\n 309→  const bot = new Telegraf(config.telegramBotToken, {...});\n 310→  registerPipelineCommands();\n 311→  // ... bot setup\n 312→}\n 313→```\n 314→\n 315→### src/utils/markdown-v2-formatter.js\n 316→```javascript\n 317→export function escapeMarkdownV2(text) {\n 318→  if (!text) return '';\n 319→  let result = text;\n 320→  for (const char of ESCAPE_CHARS) {\n 321→    result = result.split(char).join('\\\\' + char);\n 322→  }\n 323→  return result;\n 324→}\n 325→\n 326→export function formatCodeBlock(code, language = '') {...}\n 327→export function convertToMarkdownV2(markdown) {...}\n 328→```\n 329→\n 330→---\n 331→\n 332→## Section 5 — Existing Tests\n 333→\n 334→### Test Pattern (tests/bot/commands/handlers/cd.test.js)\n 335→```javascript\n 336→import { describe, test, beforeEach } from 'node:test';\n 337→import assert from 'node:assert/strict';\n 338→\n 339→describe('F-009 /cd Command Handler', () => {\n 340→  let cdHandler;\n 341→  let sessionStore;\n 342→\n 343→  beforeEach(async () => {\n 344→    const projectRoot = process.cwd();\n 345→    const cdModulePath = new URL(`file://${projectRoot}/src/bot/commands/handlers/cd.js`);\n 346→    const module = await import(cdModulePath.href);\n 347→    cdHandler = module;\n 348→  });\n 349→\n 350→  describe('cdMeta', () => {\n 351→    test('should export cdMeta with command metadata', async () => {\n 352→      assert.ok(cdHandler.cdMeta);\n 353→      assert.equal(cdHandler.cdMeta.name, 'cd');\n 354→    });\n 355→  });\n 356→\n 357→  describe('handleCd', () => {\n 358→    test('should update session cwd with valid directory', async () => {\n 359→      const replies = [];\n 360→      const handlerCtx = {\n 361→        reply: (msg) => replies.push(msg),\n 362→        sessionId: 'test-session',\n 363→        args: ['/tmp']\n 364→      };\n 365→      await handleCd(handlerCtx);\n 366→      // assertions...\n 367→    });\n 368→  });\n 369→});\n 370→```\n 371→\n 372→---\n 373→\n 374→## Implementation Notes\n 375→\n 376→### Key Design Decisions\n 377→1. Use Node.js native `os` module and `child_process` for system info (no heavy dependencies)\n 378→2. Store alert rules in JSON file under `data/` directory for persistence\n 379→3. Use `setInterval` for monitoring checks, with configurable interval\n 380→4. Format output as Markdown tables for Telegram display\n 381→5. Integrate with existing permission system (F-006) for /kill command\n 382→\n 383→### File Structure to Create\n 384→```\n 385→src/\n 386→├── services/\n 387→│   ├── system-monitor-service.js    # Core monitoring logic\n 388→│   └── alert-manager-service.js     # Alert rule management\n 389→├── bot/commands/handlers/\n 390→│   ├── sysinfo.js                   # /sysinfo command\n 391→│   ├── ps.js                        # /ps command\n 392→│   ├── kill.js                      # /kill command\n 393→│   └── monitor.js                   # /monitor command\n 394→data/\n 395→└── alert-rules.json                 # Persistent alert rules\n 396→tests/\n 397→├── services/\n 398→│   ├── system-monitor-service.test.js\n 399→│   └── alert-manager-service.test.js\n 400→└── bot/commands/handlers/\n 401→    ├── sysinfo.test.js\n 402→    ├── ps.test.js\n 403→    ├── kill.test.js\n 404→    └── monitor.test.js\n 405→```\n 406→\n 407→### Config Additions Needed\n 408→```javascript\n 409→// In config.js schema\n 410→SYSTEM_MONITOR_INTERVAL_MS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(60000),\n 411→SYSTEM_MONITOR_DATA_DIR: z.string().optional().default('data'),\n 412→```\n 413→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce3c0133387a67221a0dc484f071a","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T20:44:45.752Z","_requestId":"d34d194674fe4df2b045b65a2435281c"}
{"type":"assistant","uuid":"202603130444455be277ae5023493f","session_id":"301af3e8-7399-4356-b525-ec1e2117384a","message":{"id":"202603130444455be277ae5023493f","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019ce3cb7317df966f3c1af348b0a7cd","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/012-system-monitor/context-snapshot.md","new_string":"### Config Additions Needed\n```javascript\n// In config.js schema\nSYSTEM_MONITOR_INTERVAL_MS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(60000),\nSYSTEM_MONITOR_DATA_DIR: z.string().optional().default('data'),\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Log\n\n### Files Created\n| Path | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `src/services/system-monitor-service.js` | Core system monitoring - CPU, memory, disk, network, process management |\n| `src/services/alert-manager-service.js` | Alert rule management, threshold checking, persistence |\n| `src/bot/commands/handlers/sysinfo.js` | `/sysinfo` command handler |\n| `src/bot/commands/handlers/ps.js` | `/ps` command handler with sorting and filtering |\n| `src/bot/commands/handlers/kill.js` | `/kill` command handler with confirmation flow |\n| `src/bot/commands/handlers/monitor.js` | `/monitor` command handler for alert management |\n| `tests/services/system-monitor-service.test.js` | 23 unit tests for SystemMonitorService |\n| `tests/services/alert-manager-service.test.js` | 30 unit tests for AlertManagerService |\n| `tests/bot/commands/handlers/sysinfo.test.js` | 7 tests for sysinfo handler |\n| `tests/bot/commands/handlers/ps.test.js` | 12 tests for ps handler |\n| `tests/bot/commands/handlers/kill.test.js` | 10 tests for kill handler |\n| `tests/bot/commands/handlers/monitor.test.js` | 13 tests for monitor handler |\n| `tests/integration/f012-system-monitor.test.js` | 7 integration tests |\n| `data/alert-rules.json` | Initial empty alert rules file |\n\n### Files Modified\n| Path | Changes |\n|------|---------|\n| `src/config.js` | Added `SYSTEM_MONITOR_INTERVAL_MS` and `SYSTEM_MONITOR_DATA_DIR` config options |\n| `src/security/permission-guard.js` | Added `kill` to HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS, added `sysinfo`, `ps`, `monitor`, `kill` to COMMAND_MIN_ROLE |\n| `src/bot/telegram.js` | Imported and registered new command handlers |\n| `.prizm-docs/runtime.prizm` | Added new files, interfaces, TRAPS, and DECISIONS for F-012 |\n| `.prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm` | Added system monitor and alert manager public APIs |\n\n### Key Implementation Decisions\n\n1. **Cross-platform Support**: SystemMonitorService handles both Unix (macOS/Linux) and Windows platforms with appropriate commands (`ps aux` vs `tasklist`, `df` vs `wmic`).\n\n2. **Alert Rule Format**: Simple string format `metric>threshold` (e.g., `cpu>80`, `memory>=90`) for easy user input, parsed by `parseRuleString()`.\n\n3. **Cooldown Mechanism**: 5-minute default cooldown between repeated alerts for the same rule to prevent notification spam.\n\n4. **Process Kill Safety**: \n   - Requires admin role (`minRole: 'admin'`)\n   - Added to `HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS` requiring confirmation\n   - Uses existing confirmation manager from F-006\n   - Logs to audit trail\n\n5. **Output Formatting**: Uses tree-style formatting (├ └) instead of tables for better Telegram MarkdownV2 compatibility.\n\n6. **No New Dependencies**: All functionality uses Node.js built-in modules (`os`, `child_process`, `fs/promises`, `crypto`).\n\n### Test Coverage\n- **102 F-012 specific tests pass** (all new tests)\n- Total test suite: 1071 pass, 13 pre-existing failures (unrelated to F-012)\n\n### Deviations from Plan\n- None. Implementation follows plan.md interface design exactly.","old_string":"### Config Additions Needed\n```javascript\n// In config.js schema\nSYSTEM_MONITOR_INTERVAL_MS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(60000),\nSYSTEM_MONITOR_DATA_DIR: z.string().optional().default('data'),\n```"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"