ommands/handlers/ps.test.js`\n  86→- [x] Create `tests/bot/commands/handlers/kill.test.js`\n  87→- [x] Create `tests/bot/commands/handlers/monitor.test.js`\n  88→- [x] Test metadata, handler function, output formatting\n  89→\n  90→### T-4.4: Integration Tests\n  91→- [x] Create `tests/integration/f012-system-monitor.test.js`\n  92→- [x] Test full command flow from Telegram to response\n  93→- [x] Test permission enforcement\n  94→- [x] Test confirmation flow for /kill\n  95→\n  96→## Phase 5: Documentation & Finalization\n  97→\n  98→### T-5.1: Update Prizm Docs\n  99→- [x] Update `.prizm-docs/runtime.prizm` with new commands\n 100→- [x] Update `.prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm` with new services\n 101→- [x] Add TRAPS for monitoring and process management\n 102→\n 103→### T-5.2: Create Data Directory\n 104→- [x] Create `data/` directory if not exists\n 105→- [x] Create initial empty `data/alert-rules.json`\n 106→- [x] Add `.gitkeep` to data directory\n 107→\n 108→### T-5.3: Final Verification\n 109→- [x] Run all tests: `npm test`\n 110→- [ ] Manual test all commands in Telegram (requires manual testing)\n 111→- [ ] Verify alert notifications work correctly (requires manual testing)\n 112→- [ ] Check persistence after bot restart (requires manual testing)\n 113→\n 114→---\n 115→\n 116→## Task Dependencies\n 117→\n 118→```\n 119→T-1.1 ─┬─► T-2.1 ─► T-4.3 (sysinfo)\n 120→       ├─► T-2.2 ─► T-4.3 (ps)\n 121→       └─► T-2.3 ─► T-4.3 (kill)\n 122→              ▲\n 123→T-3.1 ────────┘\n 124→\n 125→T-1.2 ─► T-2.4 ─► T-4.3 (monitor)\n 126→   │\n 127→   └─► T-4.2\n 128→\n 129→T-1.3 ─► T-1.2\n 130→\n 131→T-4.1, T-4.2, T-4.3 ─► T-4.4 ─► T-5.3\n 132→```\n 133→\n 134→## Notes\n 135→\n 136→- TDD approach: Write tests first, then implementation\n 137→- Each task should be completable in one session\n 138→- Mark tasks `[x]` immediately after completion\n 139→- Update context-snapshot.md with Implementation Log when done\n 140→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_u