for large process lists\n  40→- [x] Register command in telegram.js\n  41→\n  42→### T-2.3: Create /kill Handler\n  43→- [x] Create `src/bot/commands/handlers/kill.js`\n  44→- [x] Define command metadata (name, description, minRole: admin)\n  45→- [x] Add to HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS requiring confirmation\n  46→- [x] Implement confirmation flow integration\n  47→- [x] Add audit logging for kill actions\n  48→- [x] Register command in telegram.js\n  49→\n  50→### T-2.4: Create /monitor Handler\n  51→- [x] Create `src/bot/commands/handlers/monitor.js`\n  52→- [x] Define command metadata with subcommands\n  53→- [x] Implement `set` subcommand: `/monitor set cpu>80`\n  54→- [x] Implement `list` subcommand: `/monitor list`\n  55→- [x] Implement `remove` subcommand: `/monitor remove <id>`\n  56→- [x] Implement `enable/disable` subcommands\n  57→- [x] Register command in telegram.js\n  58→\n  59→## Phase 3: Permission & Security\n  60→\n  61→### T-3.1: Update Permission Guard\n  62→- [x] Add `kill` to `COMMAND_MIN_ROLE` with 'admin' role\n  63→- [x] Add `kill` to `HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS` set\n  64→- [x] Add `sysinfo`, `ps`, `monitor` to `COMMAND_MIN_ROLE`\n  65→\n  66→## Phase 4: Tests\n  67→\n  68→### T-4.1: SystemMonitorService Tests\n  69→- [x] Create `tests/services/system-monitor-service.test.js`\n  70→- [x] Test `getSystemInfo()` returns valid structure\n  71→- [x] Test `getProcessList()` with sorting and filtering\n  72→- [x] Test `killProcess()` error handling\n  73→- [x] Test cross-platform compatibility (mock platform checks)\n  74→\n  75→### T-4.2: AlertManagerService Tests\n  76→- [x] Create `tests/services/alert-manager-service.test.js`\n  77→- [x] Test rule CRUD operations\n  78→- [x] Test persistence (save/load)\n  79→- [x] Test threshold detection logic\n  80→- [x] Test monitoring start/stop\n  81→- [x] Test cooldown mechanism\n  82→\n  83→### T-4.3: Command Handler Tests\n  84→- [x] Create `tests/bot/commands/handlers/sysinfo.test.js`\n  85→- [x] Create `tests/bot/commands/handlers/ps.test.js`\n  86→- [x] Create `tests/bot/commands/handlers/kill.test.js`\n  87→- [x] Create `tests/bot/commands/handlers/monitor.test.js`\n  88→- [x] Test metadata, handler function, output formatting\n  89→\n  90→### T-4.4: Integration Tests\n  91→- [x] Create `tests/integration/f012-system-monitor.test.js`\n  92→- [x] Test full command flow from Telegram to response\n  93→- [x] Test permission enforcement\n  94→- [x] Test confirmation flow for /kill\n  95→\n  96→## Phase 5: Documentation & Finalization\n  97→\n  98→### T-5.1: Update Prizm Docs\n  99→- [x] Update `.prizm-docs/runtime.prizm` with new commands\n 100→- [x] Update `.prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm` with new services\n 101→- [x] Add TRAPS for monitoring and process management\n 102→\n 103→### T-5.2: Create Data Directory\n 104→- [x] Create `data/` directory if not exists\n 105→- [x] Create initial empty `data/alert-rules.json`\n 106→- [x] Add `.gitkeep` to data directory\n 107→\n 108→### T-5.3: Final Verification\n 109→- [x] Run all tests: `npm test`\n 110→- [ ] Manual test all commands in Telegram (requires manual testing)\n 111→- [ ] Verify alert notifications work correctly (requires manual testing)\n 112→- [ ] Check persistence after bot restart (requires manual testing)\n 113→\n 114→---\n 115→\n 116→## Task Dependencies\n 117→\n 118→```\n 119→T-1.1 ─┬─► T-2.1 ─► T-4.3 (sysinfo)\n 120→       ├─► T-2.2 ─► T-4.3 (ps)\n 121→       └─► T-2.3 ─► T-4.3 (kill)\n 122→              ▲\n 123→T-3.1 ────────┘\n 124→\n 125→T-1.2 ─► T-2.4 ─► T-4.3 (monitor)\n 126→   │\n 127→   └─► T-4.2\n 128→\n 129→T-1.3 ─► T-1.2\n 130→\n 131→T-4.1, T-4.2, T-4.3 ─► T-4.4 ─► T-5.3\n 132→```\n 133→\n 134→## Notes\n 135→\n 136→- TDD approach: Write tests first, then implementation\n 137→- Each task should be completable in one session\n 138→- Mark tasks `[x]` immediately after completion\n 139→- Update context-snapshot.md with Implementation Log when done\n 140→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_u