{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260313044747b380cc3dc5b04170","session_id":"301af3e8-7399-4356-b525-ec1e2117384a","message":{"id":"20260313044747b380cc3dc5b04170","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## F-012: System Monitor - Implementation Complete\n\n### Summary\n\nSuccessfully implemented Feature F-012 (System Monitor) with all acceptance criteria met.\n\n### What Was Built\n\n**New Commands:**\n| Command | Description | Permission |\n|---------|-------------|------------|\n| `/sysinfo` | System overview (CPU, memory, disk, network) | viewer |\n| `/ps [--sort=cpu\\|memory] [--filter=keyword]` | Process list with sorting/filtering | viewer |\n| `/kill <pid>` | Terminate process | admin + confirmation |\n| `/monitor set\\|list\\|remove\\|enable\\|disable` | Alert rule management | viewer |\n\n**New Services:**\n- `system-monitor-service.js` - Core system metrics collection using Node.js native `os` module\n- `alert-manager-service.js` - Threshold monitoring with persistent rules\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Cross-platform support (Unix/Windows)\n- Alert rules persisted in `data/alert-rules.json`\n- 5-minute cooldown prevents notification spam\n- Integration with F-006 permission system for `/kill` safety\n\n### Test Results\n- **102 F-012 specific tests: ALL PASS**\n- Full test suite: 1071 pass, 13 fail (pre-existing, unrelated to F-012)\n\n### Commit\n```\nc1a584b feat(F-012): System Monitor\n21 files changed, 2719 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)\n```\n\n### Session Status\n- **Status**: success\n- **Completed Phases**: 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5\n- **Tasks**: 47/47 complete\n- **Checkpoint**: CP-2 reached"}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":91255,"output_tokens":365,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"__timestamp":"2026-03-12T20:47:55.008Z","_requestId":"d34d194674fe4df2b045b65a